### Quest Lines ###


## Quest Line: Modpack Introduction
betterquesting.questline.emycLOaLQJyuHL693zRL0g.name=Modpack Introduction
betterquesting.questline.emycLOaLQJyuHL693zRL0g.desc=Welcome to the modpack!

# Quest: Additional NTM Modes
betterquesting.quest.-haXUJ5EQD-cNU0TZtxV0g.name=Additional NTM Modes
betterquesting.quest.-haXUJ5EQD-cNU0TZtxV0g.desc=§dNTM§r offers a very modular config file, which also comes with additional modes one can activate. These can be enabled in the hbm.cfg file.%n%n§2Expensive Mode§r makes everything more expensive by requiring not only more resourses, but also new components. The quest book will not reflect the changes in progression if its enabled.%n%n§2528 Mode§r introduces gates in the form of templates which are unlocked by destroying a certain amount of items in an §3Annihilator§r. Additionally, some items, mainly circuits, are percentage based now to be crafted. Along with that, theres also more changes that make the game harder, such as §6Tantalum§r generating in a certain area, landmines spawning more frequently and all §dAE2§r blocks §4EXPLODE§r when used.%n%nMany recycling probabilities of the §3Precision Assembler§r are massively lowered with expensive mode enabled, increasing effective cost massively.%n%n§2Rampant Mode§r makes glyphids a very big threat as pollution now makes them way stronger and more aggresive. New more destructive types of glyphids will also become more common. If high enough pollution has been reached, glyphid scouts can spawn passively, which makes automated defense systems necessary as to prevent new hives from being created.%n%n§2328 Mode§r§r is the combination fo the previous 3 modes and is the hardest challenge one can attempt.%n%n§2For modes with recipe changes, the modpack's recipes have to be inserted again after a new hbmrecipes folder has been created and modes enabled.§r%n

# Quest: Modpack Introduction
betterquesting.quest.3G7SDsaNR4a8CT-MMOFJgg.name=Modpack Introduction
betterquesting.quest.3G7SDsaNR4a8CT-MMOFJgg.desc=Welcome to §5Nuclear Tech: Integrated§r! %n%nPlease read the following information before starting out.%n%n1) Manually updating §3§dNTM§r will cause new/changed recipes to not load. To update either wait for a new pack release, or better yet, head over to the config folder to the file named "Custom Recipes" and read the instructions form there.%n%n2) Remember to Claim your base and Chunkload your reactors using §3§dServer Utilities§r (from the inventory).%n%n3) Normal world generation is available in the world creation tab for those that feel like §3§dRTG§r may be affecting their performance.%n%n4) If shaders are glitching out try to use fancy textures.%n%n5) If you are encountering any rendering problems, try to scroll around in §dNEI§r.%n%nThis version of the Quest book was made by _SkippyPlaysMC_ on NTM version X5719.%n%n§4Do not use the quests for a modpack that is to be published, unless given explicit permission.§r%n%n§a§2Special thanks to everyone on discord who helped out with questions and recommendations while making the quests, aswell as the official NTM Wiki for providing information used in the quests.

# Quest: Additional Modpack Information
betterquesting.quest.KB3dBT-nRp6btinFrnJXkg.name=Additional Modpack Information
betterquesting.quest.KB3dBT-nRp6btinFrnJXkg.desc=§5Nuclear Tech: Integrated§r comes packed with many qol mods aswell as some mods that arent very apparent at first.%n%n1) §dSimpleHarvest§r allows for crop harvesting without breaking the crop itself, simply by just right clicking.%n%n2) §dRandomThings§r adds Blood Moons, semi-rare events where mob spawning is increased and the player cant sleep. Blood Moons can be quite useful, if one is prepared, as rare mob drops such as §6Launch Codes§r and §6Geiger Counters§r can be obtained early on.%n%n3) §dMutant Creatures§r adds rare spawning buffed base minecraft mobs which have had their attack strength and health increased.

# Quest: Nature's Compass
betterquesting.quest.TCSwirb4QWe9becAfFkylw.name=Nature's Compass
betterquesting.quest.TCSwirb4QWe9becAfFkylw.desc=A §dNature's Compass§r can be used to easily locate biomes of interest.

# Quest: Backpacks and Exploration
betterquesting.quest.ThViNfMEQC2vMD1tN0F4rg.name=Backpacks and Exploration
betterquesting.quest.ThViNfMEQC2vMD1tN0F4rg.desc=Exploration is an important part of the §dNTM§r experience as salvaging abandoned structures is a viable strategy for early game.%n%n§dBackpacks§r will be a massive help, as they can be used to carry around more loot. Crates can also be used to transport items, but backpacks also come packed with dedicated tool slots, a crafting table, a bed aswell as fluid tanks.%n%nA §6Hose§r can be used to quickly input and output fluids stored in the backpack.

# Quest: Off-Hand
betterquesting.quest._hMHErY_R-2HhEWC8iOYUA.name=Off-Hand
betterquesting.quest._hMHErY_R-2HhEWC8iOYUA.desc=§dBackhand§r§r backports minecraft's off-hand. Use your off-hand to hold torches, or even food while mining.%n%nLarge caverns also exist in this modpack, so dont hesistate going caving.

# Quest: Inventory Management
betterquesting.quest.dSSo1iITRNiencxnP_dGQw.name=Inventory Management
betterquesting.quest.dSSo1iITRNiencxnP_dGQw.desc=§dFindIt§r allows one to find any item stored in their storage area. Hover over the item of choice in NEI and press §6T§r. The container will become outlined.%n%n§6Holo Glasses§r will visualise the contents of an inventory when looking at them. Equip them either in the head armor slot, or one of the baubles slot available from the button next to the player model in the inventory. They can be toggled on and off by the use of a keybind.

# Quest: BetterQuesting
betterquesting.quest.yAANgk0sR0WzEjsNHwpfPA.name=BetterQuesting
betterquesting.quest.yAANgk0sR0WzEjsNHwpfPA.desc=If you are playing with friends, make sure to invite them in your BetterQuesting Party as to share progression and rewards.%n%nThis quest book does not contain all the content from the mod, such as the guns, many armor sets and others. Make sure to browse NEI.%n%nWhen updating the modpack to newer versions that has introduced changes to the quest book, in case the quests dont update or complete, delete the betterquesting folder in the world file.%nAfter it is deleted, turn on cheats and do "/bq_admin edit true", head over to the chapter of your choice, press the designer button (the one with many squares), click on your quest of choice and finally press the autocomplete button (checkmark) to complete the quests previously completed.


## Quest Line: NTM: Early Game
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA.name=NTM: Early Game
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA.desc=This is the beginning of HBM's Nuclear Tech mod. In this chapter you will learn about the basic mechanics of the mod, aswell as tips and tricks to help you progress.

# Quest: Storage Drawers
betterquesting.quest.-7rSSbm6Q-qSPUPH2dapXA.name=Storage Drawers
betterquesting.quest.-7rSSbm6Q-qSPUPH2dapXA.desc=Storage Drawers§r are an easy and cheap way of storing large amounts of items. They can be further upgraded to increase storage capacity aswell as other abilities, such as voiding. They can also be §dChiseled§r to change their wood type.%n%nA §3Framing Table§r can be used to design drawers based on any block.%n%n§2Many drawers may cause lag.

# Quest: Stirling Engine
betterquesting.quest.-OxoBRz7Spqm0rVUNxRVpA.name=Stirling Engine
betterquesting.quest.-OxoBRz7Spqm0rVUNxRVpA.desc=The §3Stirling Engine§r uses heat from a §3Heating Oven§r or a §3§r§3Firebox§r to produce power. If a Heating Oven is used to heat a Stirling engine, it will likely over-speed and damage it, sending the main gear flying. The heavy Stirling engine does not have this issue.%n%nA firebox running on coal with a stirling engine produces §e2kHE/s§r, while a heating oven with a heavy stirling engine produces §e10kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Waystones
betterquesting.quest.-YTKfE9oSJuVowjvBCNvsA.name=Waystones
betterquesting.quest.-YTKfE9oSJuVowjvBCNvsA.desc=§dWaystones§r are a method of teleporation that work in one dimension. They can be set to global to make them accessable by othe players. Additionally, the §dWarpstone§r can be used to teleport to any waystone from anywhere at the cost of a 5m cooldown.

# Quest: Steam Engine
betterquesting.quest.1WdjJYUsRMKgt4MYnlmM7A.name=Steam Engine
betterquesting.quest.1WdjJYUsRMKgt4MYnlmM7A.desc=The §3Steam Engine§r is an early game method of turning §bSteam§r into energy. It requires an external source to provide steam and a way to dump or reprocess the §bLow-Pressure Steam§r it produces. %n%nThe Steam Engine has an energy efficiency of §e85%%§r, making it better than the §3Stirling Engine§r. However, it still has a throughput limit as it can only hold up to 2000 mB of steam. Its maximum processing rate is 2000 mB/t, producing a considerable §e3400 HE/t§r or §e68 kHE/s§r. It is therefore the best generator available before §3Steam Turbines§r.%n%nA boiler being heated up by a heating oven using coal will produce §e17kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Armor Modifications
betterquesting.quest.3J7vD46NQg6IMMDRALpT-A.name=Armor Modifications
betterquesting.quest.3J7vD46NQg6IMMDRALpT-A.desc=The §3Armor Modification Table§r allows for armor modifications to be inserted in armor, giving either buffs, new abilities or extra resistance.

# Quest: Additional Fluid Tools
betterquesting.quest.9RM80ygPQTaxxeDb0-qGtw.name=Additional Fluid Tools
betterquesting.quest.9RM80ygPQTaxxeDb0-qGtw.desc=The §6Siphon§r is a tool used to extract input fluids from a machine. Right-clicking a machine with content in it's input tanks will fill any fluid barrels, universal tanks or pipettes (if the fluid amount cannot fill any of the previous options).%n%n§6Pipettes§r can be used to input specific amounts of fluids. Right-clicking or Shift-Right-clicking will increase or decrease the fluid amount.

# Quest: Automatic Buzz Saw
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0A.name=Automatic Buzz Saw
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0A.desc=With the §6§3Automatic Buzz Saw§r one can automatically farm trees for their §6Wood§r. If jungle trees are farmed, §6Latex§r automation is also possible.%n%n§3Fans§r, when powered by redstone, can be used to push the dropped items into hoppers or conveyors for storage. Use a §6Drill§r on them to remove the diminishing pushing range.

# Quest: Industrial Mixer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0w.name=Industrial Mixer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0w.desc=The §3Industrial Mixer§r is a machine that is used to mix a fluid with an item and/or another fluid. It can be used instead of a §3Chemical Plant§r for some recipes.

# Quest: NTM: Introduction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQ.name=NTM: Introduction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQ.desc=This is the begining of the tech tree of §dHBM's Nuclear Tech Mod§r. Before proceeding it is recommended that you stock up on materials such as §6Iron§r, §6Coal§r, §6Copper§r and §6Redstone§r.%n%n§a§2Some advanced machinery can be obtained by salvaging them from structures scattered across the world, such as Centrifuges from abandoned nuclear powerplants found in deserts, or by rare mob drops such as a Geiger Counter.§r%n%nThe NTM Wiki link can be found here:%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Main_Page[/url]

# Quest: Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAw.name=Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAw.desc=§3Anvils§r are a tiered crafting station that allows for the creation of various machines, structures, and items in some cases. There are multiple tiers of anvils with greater anvil tier primarily corresponding to a greater quantity of recipes being available.%n%nStamps, used in the §3Burner Press§r, are made in the anvil. A plate stamp is required for the §3Blast Furnace§r.

# Quest: Burner Press
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABA.name=Burner Press
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABA.desc=The §3Presses§r are machines that can be used to make §6Plates§r, §6Wires§r, §6Circuits§r, §6Bullet Casings§r as well as §6Compressing§r non-smeltable powders back into their normal form. They require §6Stamps§r to work, which can be made from an §3Anvil§r.%n%n§2A preheater can be placed next to the Burner Press to increase its speed.

# Quest: Glyphids
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABQ.name=Glyphids
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABQ.desc=§6Glyphids§r are large insects that have many different types. They primarily spawn with naturally generated §6§rhives§r structures. All of the types are armored and they take less damage than against normal mobs. Glyphids are normally attracted to pollution created by the player, and usually have to be dealt with by the player.%n%n§6§r§6Hives§r can spawn naturally in all non-ocean biomes and can also be created by glyphid scouts. They contain several glyphid egg blocks and some low-tier loot inside, lying on top of eggs. glyphid egg blocks spawn glyphids and drop glyphid eggs upon destruction.%n%n§2It is recommended that all hives are destroyed as soon as possible as to prevent their spread later on.

# Quest: Blast Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQ.name=Blast Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQ.desc=The §3Blast Furnace§r is a solid fuel-powered furnace used to create different alloys out of two inputs. The main starter alloys are: §6Minecraft Grade Copper§r and §6Steel§r. Inserting §bHot Air Blast§r, made by putting §bCompressed Air§r in a §3Boiler§r, grants all recipes a §e3x§r boost.%n§bFlue Gas§r produced from operating the machine can be burnt for energy or vented into the atmosphere.%n%nSteel tools come equiped with vein mining, making them an excellent early-game tool.%n%n§2For more advanced tools later on, pressing the ALT key will bring up a menu from which one can select multiple abilities at once.§r

# Quest: Trench Mask
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADA.name=Trench Mask
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADA.desc=The §6Trench Mask§r is a basic mask that will protect the user from some dangerous airborne particles while mining. To craft one you must first obtain §6Cloth§r and then piss on it by right clicking while holding it.%n%n§2String can be easily obtained by harvesting Hemp, found in the wild.

# Quest: Hazmat Suits
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADw.name=Hazmat Suits
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADw.desc=§6Hazmat Suits§r provide protection against many hazards, mainly radiation. §6Hazmat Cloth§r can be further strengthened to create more resistant hazmat suits.%n%nTo provide additional protection against environmental dangers, a §6Gas Mask Filter§r is needed, which can be equiped by right-clicking while holding it.

# Quest: Energy Cables
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQ.name=Energy Cables
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQ.desc=The most basic block for transmission is the §3Red Copper Cable§r, which comes in two varieties, a block form and a skinnier cable form. The block form also has a paintable version which can help it blend into your designs better.%n%nFor better looking, aswell as longer distance energy transportation, a §l§r§6Cable Drum§r with §3Electricity Connectors§r can be used. These powerlines are non solid and can also pass through floors and walls.%n%n

# Quest: Pollution Detector
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEg.name=Pollution Detector
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEg.desc=The §6Pollution Detector§r will monitor and show the levels of pollution present in the environment. High levels of pollution will decrease the visibility, give debuffs to the player and buff mobs, including skeletons spawning with firearms.

# Quest: Wood-Burning Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEw.name=Wood-Burning Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEw.desc=The §3Wood-Burning Generator§r is basic method of producing energy by burning wood. It can run on any burnable items but provides burn time bonuses to logs and wood. It can also run on any flammable fuel by clicking on the arrow below the on/off switch, but it is considerably more inefficient than other fluid burning generators.%n%nBurning logs in the generator produces §e2kHE/s.§r

# Quest: Analog Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFA.name=Analog Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFA.desc=The §6Analog Circuit§r is the first true circuit board used in crafting certain essential machines and tools such as the §6Oil Deposit Detector§r, the §3Chemical Plant§r, and the §3Electric Arc Furnace§r.%n%n§2A cheaper recipe for Capacitors will be available if a Shredder is owned.

# Quest: Assembly Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQ.name=Assembly Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQ.desc=The §3Assembly Machine§r is used in every stage of the game, with it being used to manufacture practically every other complex machine. Recipes for it can be chosen inside the GUI.

# Quest: Shredder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGg.name=Shredder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGg.desc=The §3Shredder§r is a machine that shreds resourses into their powder form, or in many cases, their crafting materials. It can also be used to double ores.%n%n§2Shredder blades are require in order for the machine to work.

# Quest: Soldering Station
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHA.name=Soldering Station
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHA.desc=The §3Soldering Station§r is the machine in which §6§rcircuit components§r can be combined§6§r into §6Circuits§r and where §6Machine Upgrades§r can be created.

# Quest: Crucible
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHQ.name=Crucible
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHQ.desc=The §3Crucible§r is an important machine as it is the central component of metallurgy. It is used as a method of ore processing, alloying, and metal casting. It requires an external heat source to melt the inputs into liquids and when filled, it emits a consistent amount of soot that can cause a fair amount of pollution that cannot be mitigated. Some alloys, as mentioned before, can be made alternatively using a §3Blast Furnace§r, however this is generally slower.%n%n[F1] For more information.%n%nIt is recommended that the wiki is checked out.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Crucible[/url]

# Quest: Arc Welder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHw.name=Arc Welder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHw.desc=The §3Arc Welder§r is a machine needed for the creation of many components, such as §6Welded Plates§r, §6Missile Parts§r and more. Some Recipes will require a fluid inserted into the welder to work.

# Quest: Combination Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQ.name=Combination Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQ.desc=The §3Combination Oven§r is a unique type of furnace that transforms items into their respective product and produce liquid byproducts. It can be used to produce §6Coke§r, §bWood Oil§r and §6Aluminium§r more efficiently. 

# Quest: Chemical Plant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIg.name=Chemical Plant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIg.desc=The §3Chemical Plant§r is a machine needed for several processes, turning fluids into other fluids, synthesis of different compounds, ect. Like the §3Assembly Machine§r, recipes can be selected entirely within the GUI.

# Quest: Strand Caster
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJA.name=Strand Caster
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJA.desc=The §3Strand Caster§r is a large basin that can cast items in batches of 9. It also requires §bWater§r in order to cast, where it makes §bLow-Pressure Steam§r that can be turned back into water.

# Quest: High-Speed Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJQ.name=High-Speed Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJQ.desc=High-speed steel§r is an advanced and specialized form of standard steel. It used in many recipes, such as the §3Oil Derrick§r and the §3Industrial Mixer§r.

# Quest: Oil Resevoir Detector
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJg.name=Oil Resevoir Detector
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJg.desc=The §6Oil Resevoir Detector§r will help one in the search for an §eOil Deposit§r by pointing it out in chat. If the oil deposit is located very far away, it can be mined and moved to a stationary oil refinery.

# Quest: Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKg.name=Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKg.desc=§3Conveyors§r provide the simplest way of moving items around. There are multiple blocks that can interface with machines as well as items moving along conveyor belts.%n%n§3Conveyor Belts§r are blocks used to transport items. They can pick up dropped items or items from conveyor ejectors. Conveyor inserters can take items from conveyor belts. If there are no conveyor inserters present, the item will be dropped at the end of the conveyor belt line.%n%n§3Conveyor Inserters§r are blocks that take items from conveyor belts and outputs them into a storage space. Conveyor ejectors are the opposite, they take items from storage and place them onto conveyor belts. %n%nInserters have an option to destroy surplus items if the input buffer has run full, otherwise the items that can neither be inserted in the target nor the inserter's buffer is simply dropped.%n%nThe ejector has a whitelist/blacklist system (the default mode is blacklist with no restrictions - this means that everything will go through). Rick-clicking the white arrow will toggle between whitelist and blacklist. An item can be added to the blacklist/whitelist by "depositing" it into the blue inventory square - the item will not be consumed, however.%n%nThe §3Conveyor Splitter§r is a type of conveyor belt that splits items evenly onto 2 lanes.%n%n§3Conveyor Sorters§r are blocks that can sort various items to a specific conveyor belt. They do not have a buffer and simple move items to connected conveyor belts based on their filter options, therefore they can sort items as quickly as they receive them.%nThe sorter has six outputs with five slots each, making it able to route multiple items to one belt.

# Quest: Settings Tool
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMQ.name=Settings Tool
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMQ.desc=The §6Settings Tool§r is used to copy settings of machines. It is especially useful when making large refineries.

# Quest: Rotary Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPQ.name=Rotary Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPQ.desc=The §3Rotary Furnace§r is a large furnace which is powered by both §bSteam§r and §6§rsolid fuel. §rIt outputs molten material which can be cast similarly to the outputs of the §3Crucible§r and §3Arc Furnace§r. The Rotary Furnace is the only machine that can produce §6Saturnite§r and §6Weapon Steel§r.

# Quest: Boiler and Steam Condenser
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVQ.name=Boiler and Steam Condenser
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVQ.desc=The §3Boiler§r, when receiving heat from below, heats up fluids. Two important uses of the boiler are for §bSteam§r and §bOil§r processing which will come later on. The Boiler can explode if its output is full.%n%nSteam, when used by machines, such as reactors sending steam through §3Turbines§r or §3Chemical Factories§r produce §bLow-Pressure Steam§r. The low-pressure steam can be recycled back to retrieve 100%% of the water by using a §3Steam Condenser§r. Closed water loops are recommended for reactors.

# Quest: Solar Tower Boiler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYg.name=Solar Tower Boiler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYg.desc=The §3Solar Tower Boiler§r is an earlygame machine that can use sunlight from heliostat mirrors to boil water.%n%nThe Solar Tower Boiler gets heat from heliostat mirrors pointed at it. Aiming a mirror at the boiler can be done using the mirror adjustment tool, right-click on the boiler will save its position to the tool, and subsequently clicking on mirrors will aim them at the linked boiler. The maximum range for mirrors is 25 blocks, mirror efficiency does not degrade with range. A boiler consumes 1mB of water for every 12.5 mirrors each tick at full sunlight level, and 100mB of steam per mB of water consumed. However, the water consumption rate is rounded down to the millibucket. Thus it takes 13 mirrors to raise your first 100mB/t of steam, 12 mirrors for the next hundred, then 13, 12, and so on.%n%nAs the heat provided by each mirror is based on sunlight, mirrors with solid blocks above them will not work, and the amount of heat diminishes with the amount of light in the evening until it produces no heat at night.%n%nThe solar tower boiler can only produce regular steam, and thus the liquid type cannot be changed using fluid identifiers.

# Quest: Ammo Press and Guns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAaA.name=Ammo Press and Guns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAaA.desc=With casting available through the §3Crucible§r, many gun parts can now be created such as §6Barrels§r and §6Grips§r. An §3Ammo Press§r is used to create the various ammunitions guns use.%n%nA §3Weapon Modification Table§r can be used to install weapon mods, such as §6Silencers§r and §6Scopes§r.%n%nThe §6Bullet Casing Bag§r will retrieve some of the casings when guns are fired.

# Quest: Mining Charge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhQ.name=Mining Charge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhQ.desc=The §3Mining Charge§r is an explosive made with the express purpose of mining, as such it's commonly used to mine depth ores, since it dosen't destroy drops, before getting a pickaxe that can do the same. Mining Charges are a great way of obtaining §6Zirconium§r from depth ores for nuclear fuel rods.%n%nIt has an explosion radius of about 3 blocks and explodes instantly upon being powered by redstone, while exploding it does no damage to entities.%n%nThere are two other variants of this, being the §3Timed Mining Charge§r and the §b§3Semtex Mining Charge§r, they are both timed explosives with the semtex one being stronger than the regular one and having §eFortune 3§r, meanwhile the timed mining charge does not seem to have enhanced capabilities, other than being timed and thus more convinient to use.

# Quest: Steel Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuw.name=Steel Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuw.desc=An upgraded version of the §3Anvil§r, [T2], which unlocks additional recipes.

# Quest: Smokestack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAyg.name=Smokestack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAyg.desc=The §3Smokestack§r is used to reduce pollution made from machines. §3Exhaust Pipes§r, made in anvils, can be used to transport the fumes to the Smokestack. The §3Industrial Smokestack§r is needed to produce §6Fine Soot§r, required for making §6Fullerite§r in the late game.%n%nAn §3Ashpit§r can be installed beneath the Smokestack which will collect §6Ash§r, that can be used as a cheap black dye alternative aswell as in the creation of §6Industrial Fertilizer§r.%n%nThe wiki page for pollution can be found below.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Pollution[/url]

# Quest: Player Decontaminator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABCw.name=Player Decontaminator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABCw.desc=The §3Player Decontaminator§r will remove Rads received while standing on it. It can be very cost efficient, as other methods such as §6RadAways§r require constant replenishment.

# Quest: Machine Upgrade Template
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABSA.name=Machine Upgrade Template
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABSA.desc=The §6Machine Upgrade Template§r is the baseline for all machine upgrades. Machine upgrades are not only used to increase the efficiency of machines but also to unlock new functions.%n%n§2While in the UI of a machine, hover over an upgrade on NEI to see its effects.§r

# Quest: Drainage Pipe
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABdg.name=Drainage Pipe
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABdg.desc=The §3Drainage Pipe§r allows the dumping of fluids and gasses into the environment at the cost of pollution.

# Quest: Charm of Protection
betterquesting.quest.D0bv2vfWSkK1soyqHDwqjQ.name=Charm of Protection
betterquesting.quest.D0bv2vfWSkK1soyqHDwqjQ.desc=The §6Charm of Protection§r diverts meteorites away from the player and prevents them from destoying blocks. It is recommended that one is obtained as soon as possible as to prevent costly damages in the future.

# Quest: The Nether
betterquesting.quest.FP0J62xtTreU3IFJHpFiDg.name=The Nether
betterquesting.quest.FP0J62xtTreU3IFJHpFiDg.desc=§eThe Nether§r is entirely optional for §dNTM§r progression, but is home to many resourses, such as:%n%n§6Quartz§r§r which can be used for §6Silicon§r.%n%n§6Infernal Coal§r which can be shredded for §6Coal Powder§r. A mask or suit that can protect against Carbon Dioxide is needed to mine the deposits.%n%n§6Sulfur§r needed for various chemical processes.%n%n§6Red Phosphorus§r for incendiary weaponry.%n%n§6Glowstone§r for early §bChlorine Gas§r in a §3Combination Oven§r.%n%n§6Cobalt§r can also be rarely found near the Nether Roof.%n%nThe Nether has a backround radiation of §e0.1RAD/s§r.§r%n%n§2Glowstone, Quartz and Phosphorus Bedrock Ore Deposits also exist.§r%n%n§2Depth Neodymium Deposits also spawn exclusively in the Nether.§r

# Quest: Steel Furnace
betterquesting.quest.GOACXA8jRc-SMNzk2CsNUQ.name=Steel Furnace
betterquesting.quest.GOACXA8jRc-SMNzk2CsNUQ.desc=The §3Steel Furnace§r, unlike the other furnaces, runs off of §eTU§r. It can also process up to 3 items at a time, but each slot consumes more TU, which makes it slow without a strong heat source. It also has a bonus output for ores and wood, where every smelted item gives §e25%%§r to the bonus output meter, which means every 4 items give an extra 5th item for free (§e+15 items from a single stack§r).

# Quest: Charging Station
betterquesting.quest.GgjbEvl7T9OF7WnmHdgMNA.name=Charging Station
betterquesting.quest.GgjbEvl7T9OF7WnmHdgMNA.desc=The §3Charging Station§r will charge electric tools aswell as electric suits when standing near it. Placing more next to eachother will increase the speed at which items are being recharged.

# Quest: Storage Drawer Keys
betterquesting.quest.HTaQEgJ8QCWYNMB8n7Awug.name=Storage Drawer Keys
betterquesting.quest.HTaQEgJ8QCWYNMB8n7Awug.desc=§dStorage Drawer Keys§r can be used to modify Drawers in many ways.%n%nThe §dDrawer Key locks drawers§r, so no new item types can be inserted into the drawer when its empty.%n%nThe §dConcealment Key§r hides the item icon of drawers.%n%nThe §dQuantify Key§r shows the item quantities of drawers.%n%nThe §dPersonal Key§r protects drawers from other players (outside of claims). %n

# Quest: Bobmazon
betterquesting.quest.IAP1AGA2TV-TtMAv_QMrIA.name=Bobmazon
betterquesting.quest.IAP1AGA2TV-TtMAv_QMrIA.desc=§6Bobmazon§r is an in-game shop where players can spend §6Bottle Caps§r to purchase various items such as building blocks, plants, resourses and many more. To purchase items, one must have unlocked the achievements listed below as "Ratings".

# Quest: HE to RF Converter
betterquesting.quest.JcBabPI8RzGGmai3SwlcLw.name=HE to RF Converter
betterquesting.quest.JcBabPI8RzGGmai3SwlcLw.desc=The §3HE to RF Converter§r will convert energy produced by NTM machines into usuable power for both the §dMatter Energy Network§r and §dOpenComputers§r. It has a very large internal energy buffer, so it is recommended that a Diode is used to limit throughput.

# Quest: Latex
betterquesting.quest.JzWhzfD0T2mxYD1NrT9b6A.name=Latex
betterquesting.quest.JzWhzfD0T2mxYD1NrT9b6A.desc=§6Latex§r is an early game rubber which can be used instead of normal §6Rubber§r, such as cheaper conveyors. Before the §3Press§r is unlocked, it can be made using dandelions in a crafting table.%n%n§2If a jungle biome is too far away, beach biomes provide jungle wood and saplings from palm trees.§r

# Quest: Multi Fluid Identifier
betterquesting.quest.M3mauW7uTCej4mql-Wnhqg.name=Multi Fluid Identifier
betterquesting.quest.M3mauW7uTCej4mql-Wnhqg.desc=The §6Multi Fluid Identifier§r is used to select the type of fluid one needs. Shift-Click while holding it to select a fluid.

# Quest: Packing Tape
betterquesting.quest.RBJS7D2ATpq7GUingAewuQ.name=Packing Tape
betterquesting.quest.RBJS7D2ATpq7GUingAewuQ.desc=The §6Packing Tape§r allows one to break and move drawers without all the items falling on the floor.

# Quest: Cladding
betterquesting.quest.UKkcpXk3SEWHXLIVC5VTDg.name=Cladding
betterquesting.quest.UKkcpXk3SEWHXLIVC5VTDg.desc=§6Cladding§r is one of the most important armor modifications which reduce radiation intake. It can be inserted to all armor pieces.

# Quest: Structure Looting
betterquesting.quest.VoxsH2isSheNEKaJ3_Ikgg.name=Structure Looting
betterquesting.quest.VoxsH2isSheNEKaJ3_Ikgg.desc=The §6Screwdriver§r is used to rotate conveyor blocks aswell as to create a §3Chicago Pile§r. It can also be used in combination with §6Bobby Pins§r to unlock §6Safes§r found in various structures.%n%nThe §6Crowbar§r, which is used to open crates for loot such as food and ammunition found in various structures.

# Quest: Stirling Sawmill
betterquesting.quest._qJt02i4ST2iccmkHudKCg.name=Stirling Sawmill
betterquesting.quest._qJt02i4ST2iccmkHudKCg.desc=The §3Stirling Sawmill§r uses heat to cut wooden related items, producing §6Sawdust§r in the process. Sawdust can be used to obtain §6Paper§r, and if further processed, can be turned into §6Charcoal§r in a §3Combination Oven§r.

# Quest: Air Intake
betterquesting.quest.bC_DUDpuRDy7Y0vktb-pdQ.name=Air Intake
betterquesting.quest.bC_DUDpuRDy7Y0vktb-pdQ.desc=The §3Air Intake§r, when powered, produces §bCompressed Air§r needed in §3Pneumatic Pipes§r and §bHot Air Blast§r.

# Quest: Charcoal Automation
betterquesting.quest.bCeMQCbfSO6qNCtsy9NcnA.name=Charcoal Automation
betterquesting.quest.bCeMQCbfSO6qNCtsy9NcnA.desc=§6Wood§r obtained from a tree farm can be smelted or processed in a §3Combination Oven§r to produce §6Charcoal§r, which has many uses, such as fuel for §3Furnaces§r or even the §3Blast Furnace§r, §6Flux§r or §6Carbon§r in a Crucible for §6Steel§r production, or even §6Gunpowder§r for ammunition.

# Quest: Heating Oven/Firebox
betterquesting.quest.cUWyKdzATTSYaMg1MxZqYw.name=Heating Oven/Firebox
betterquesting.quest.cUWyKdzATTSYaMg1MxZqYw.desc=The §3Firebox§r and the §3Heating Oven§r are machines capable of producing heat (§eTU§r) from solid fuels for any machines that require heat to operate.%n%nBoth machines are similar in operation. In order for them to transfer heat, another machine for receiving the heat must be placed on top, such that the copper heat plate on the receiving machine sits on top of the copper heat plate of the heat producing machine.%n%nOnce constructed, these machines can be filled with solid fuel, which will burn until either the fuel runs out, or the heat buffer is filled. No fuel will be consumed if its buffer is full — as such, both machines are fairly efficient at conserving fuel.%n%nThe primary difference in these two machines lie in their speed: the firebox burns fuel much slower at full efficiency, whilst the heating oven produces five time the heat (but eight times faster). Despite its inefficiency, the heating oven is often preferred for its much higher heat outputs and heat capacity. However, it cannot heat a stirling engine, as its base output (500 TU/t) will automatically over-speed the engine; the heavy stirling engine does not have this issue.%n%nAdditionally, the heating oven can receive heat from other heat producing machines placed underneath it: multiple can be stacked for heat-hungry machines like the crucible. The heat received, however, is halved when transferring to the machine above.

# Quest: Tungsten Reachers
betterquesting.quest.daHRIdE8RNq4usNWqdv7fQ.name=Tungsten Reachers
betterquesting.quest.daHRIdE8RNq4usNWqdv7fQ.desc=§6Tungsten Reachers§r are a utility item which, when in any slot of the inventory, reduce the radiation taken from items. They can also handle pyrophoric items.

# Quest: Advanced Enchantment Table
betterquesting.quest.fmoLTwZ4QemPTJ_pyh1YtA.name=Advanced Enchantment Table
betterquesting.quest.fmoLTwZ4QemPTJ_pyh1YtA.desc=The §dAdvanced Enchantment Table§r gives its user the ability to choose any enchantment they want, at the cost of significantly more experience.%n%n§2Since very low level books are cheap, its a great way of mass producing Pulverized Enchantment for endgame recipes.§r

# Quest: Better Furnaces
betterquesting.quest.gKQiP_zES4KokMmon9bDQg.name=Better Furnaces
betterquesting.quest.gKQiP_zES4KokMmon9bDQg.desc=The §3Bricked Furnace§r is almost the same as the vanilla furnace, but it can smelt construction materials faster, such as §6Sand§r and §6Cobblestone§r being smelted at double the speed. §6Clay§r and §6Fire Clay§r can be smelted at §e§rquadruple§r the speed, which means that making a full brick block can be done within a vanilla furnace operation. It can also make §6Charcoal§r at double the speed. It can also collect Ashes from burnt fuel.%n%nThe §3Iron Furnace§r has the base smelting speed §e20%%§r faster than the vanilla furnace, which means it can complete an operation within 8 seconds instead of 10 seconds. Besides being able to smelt faster, it consumes fuel only during operation, so the fuel is never wasted. It also has burn time bonuses for various kinds of fuel, ranging from §e+25%%§r for lignite to §e+100%%§r for solid fuel.%n%n§dEt Futurum Requiem§r also backports modern furnaces, such as the §3Smoker§r, which cooks food faster, and the §3Blast Furnace§r, which smelts ores faster.

# Quest: The End
betterquesting.quest.iaDcxhSuSUi4Kp-PSHzjew.name=The End
betterquesting.quest.iaDcxhSuSUi4Kp-PSHzjew.desc=§eThe End§r is entirely optional for §dNTM§r progression, but is home to §6Trixite§r, a unique extraterrestrial mineral that when processed can yield §6Plutonium§r, §6Cobalt§r and §6Niobium§r. The Niobium is of great interest as it is a great source for early §3Catalytic Cracking Towers§r.%n%nDue to only the main end island existing, Trixite Ore is a limited resourse.§r Trixite Crystals can also be obtained from an §6Asteroid Mining Ship§r, but it is not recommended.%n%n§dEt Futurum Requiem§r backports many modern end features, such as §eChorus Fruit§r and a respawnable §eEnder Dragon§r using §6End Crystals§r.%n%nThe §6Dragon Egg§r can also be used to create a Backpack which provides passive §eNight Vision§r, §eStrength 2§r and §eFire resistance§r, aswell as some §eRegeneration§r when on low health.%n%nEnderman farms can also be made using §3Fans§r to push the endermen into the killing zone.

# Quest: Pipe Anchors
betterquesting.quest.jOGBJWaqQxepkxcY_MRqFA.name=Pipe Anchors
betterquesting.quest.jOGBJWaqQxepkxcY_MRqFA.desc=§3Pipe Anchors§r are non solid fluid ducts which can be used instead of normal ducts.

# Quest: Compressor
betterquesting.quest.jcaOirN6QCOC50YJbil2rQ.name=Compressor
betterquesting.quest.jcaOirN6QCOC50YJbil2rQ.desc=The §3Compressor§r is a specialized multiblock machine for compressing fluids. It can perform this operation on any fluid to increase its pressure, for use in other machines. Some of these fluids are compressed into different fluids entirely as special recipes for this machine.

# Quest: Automatic Thresher
betterquesting.quest.kfQnj5gZSnGUxUmB2HCnJg.name=Automatic Thresher
betterquesting.quest.kfQnj5gZSnGUxUmB2HCnJg.desc=The §3Automatic Thresher§r harvests crops such as §6Wheat§r, §6Hemp§r, §6Sugarcane§r, ect in a 7x7 area when supplied with fuel. It will eject all items from the back.%n%n[F1] for more information.

# Quest: Pneumatic Pipes
betterquesting.quest.pTXtLJnPRu6lyiOqGVP7lw.name=Pneumatic Pipes
betterquesting.quest.pTXtLJnPRu6lyiOqGVP7lw.desc=§3Pneumatic Pipes§r are an instant form of item transportation which can cover large distances. The pipes must have a compressed gas inside them to work, the best one being compressed air which comes from an §3Air Intake§r.%n%nA §6Screwdriver§r is needed to create a connection, and right clicking on the connection with a fluid id will set the gasseous fluid it will use.

# Quest: Long Distance Energy Transportation
betterquesting.quest.s8lSFTDKSpqK44PLhdfusw.name=Long Distance Energy Transportation
betterquesting.quest.s8lSFTDKSpqK44PLhdfusw.desc=For greater distances, and improved aesthetics, a new distribution node is available, the §3Large Electricity Pylon§r.%n%n§3Substations§r are needed to step up/down the voltage that the line carries.%n%nThese Pylons can prove useful as favorable §eBedrock Ore§r or §eOil deposits§r may be located far away from the main base.%n

# Quest: Energy Storage
betterquesting.quest.zinQBRxTQ5OaRyf9vxYaEg.name=Energy Storage
betterquesting.quest.zinQBRxTQ5OaRyf9vxYaEg.desc=The §3Battery Socket§r is used to hold §6Batteries§r or §6Capacitors§r.%n%nBatteries have more energy storage, but a slower discharge time, meaning that only a small amount of stored power can be outputted to the grid.%n%nCapacitors on the other hand, have less energy storage, but a faster discharge time.


## Quest Line: NTM: Oil
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQ.name=NTM: Oil
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQ.desc=Process Oil and begin Bedrock Ore Harvesting. This chapter revolves around the refining of Oil, aswell as the creation of plastics, more advanced circuits and other strong materials.

# Quest: Balefire
betterquesting.quest.8OusetROQiyH-66QbewmNQ.name=Balefire
betterquesting.quest.8OusetROQiyH-66QbewmNQ.desc=§6Balefire§r is an extremely radioactive substance which can be used to make powerful fuels for the §3RBMK§r, aswell as §bBF Rocket Fuel§r for power production. High radiation resistant equipment is needed to hold the item. §6Thermonuclear Ashes§r can be produced sustainably as a byproduct from §bAntimatter - BF Rocket Fuel§r.%n%nThe High-Tech Bomb Defusing Device can extract balefire shards from duds.

# Quest: Aluminium Processing
betterquesting.quest.8Z2F5EPIRPGvasjKDWd4tA.name=Aluminium Processing
betterquesting.quest.8Z2F5EPIRPGvasjKDWd4tA.desc=§6Bauxide§r and §6Cryolite§r can be further processed to obtain §6Aluminium§r, with additional byproducts of §6Iron§r, §6Titanium§r and §bMercury§r.

# Quest: Cyclotron
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA1g.name=Cyclotron
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA1g.desc=The §3Cyclotron§r is a machine that bombards element powders with element boxes to get heavier elements. Operating the machine will consume§e 20MHE/s§r.%n%nIt can also create §bAntimatter§r as a byproduct for certain operations, which makes it a reliable but expensive method of large-scale advanced material production.%n%n§2Consider installing the highest level of Power Saving and Speed upgrades to reduce both recipe time and power consumption.§r

# Quest: Desh Servo Set
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACw.name=Desh Servo Set
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACw.desc=§6Desh Servos§r are an armor modification which give incredibely strong buffs when used, such as increased strength, mining speed and jump boost.

# Quest: M1TTY Environment Suit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADg.name=M1TTY Environment Suit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADg.desc=The §6M1TTY Environment Suit§r is a cheap electric armor set that comes with many abilities. It is an excellent armor set for exploring as it comes with very high speed buffs aswell as fast swimming speed.

# Quest: Electric Arc Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHg.name=Electric Arc Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHg.desc=The §3Electric Arc Furnace§r is a large automated furnace multiblock machine that can fill the role of §3Crucible§r and automated smelter, and is required for progression as it is the only machine that can produce §6Silicon§r from various sources, such as §6Sand§r, §6Flint§r, §6fiberglass§r, and §6Asbestos§r.%n%nTo operate this machine, it will require both electrical power and crafted §7§6Electrodes§r. In terms of electricity, the machine has a maximum storage capacity of §e2.5MHE§r, and consumes §e20kHE/s§r in operation, making it reasonably power hungry. In terms of the electrodes required for operation, there are four types available, and the machine must have three installed before it can operate.%n%nThis machine can operate in two different modes: Solid mode, which is the easiest to setup and use, great for initial crafting, and Liquid mode, which produces castable molten ores much like the crucible, with a small bonus to output, increasing efficiency of extraction from various ores.

# Quest: Integrated Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIA.name=Integrated Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIA.desc=The §6Integrated Circuit Board§r is the first circuit board to use §6Silicon§r, being used extensively in mid game machines, automation devices, missiles, and various small tools such as the §6Geiger Counter§r.

# Quest: Military Grade Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIw.name=Military Grade Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIw.desc=The §6Military Grade Circuit Board§r is an advanced Circuit Board used in more complicated machines, such as the §3Gas Centrifuge§r.

# Quest: Impact Drill
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKQ.name=Impact Drill
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKQ.desc=The §6Impact Drill§r is an electric pickaxe which has prebuilt enchantments and abilities on it. It is a very useful tool which will make mining way more efficient.%n%nSimilar electric tools exist for the axe and shovel.

# Quest: Derrick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKw.name=Derrick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKw.desc=The §3Oil Derrick§r extracts §bCrude Oil§r and §6§bNatural Gas§r from §eOil Deposits§r that are directly below them. When supplied with power, it will begin to drill downwards until it cannot drill further or reach an oil deposit. Upon reaching a deposit, it will continuously extract oil and gas from it until the deposit is entirely depleted.

# Quest: Basic Oil Processing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALw.name=Basic Oil Processing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALw.desc=Before §bCrude Oil§r can be processed, it must be heated up in a §3Boiler§r.%n%nThe §3Oil Refinery§r splits Hot Crude Oil(or later on §bCracked§r) into four different fluid products and one solid byproduct.%n%nAfter that, those fluids can be sent through a §3Fractioning Tower§r to obtain different kinds of fuels, such as §bKerosene§r and §bDiesel§r. A §3Fractioning Tower Seperator§r can be used to stack fractioning towers ontop of eachother.%n%nIt is recommended that the wiki is checked out.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Guide:_Petroleum_Processing[/url]%n

# Quest: Polymer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOg.name=Polymer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOg.desc=§6Polymer§r is a basic plastic material needed for many recipes. Important uses of it are the §3Centrifuge§r, the §3Catalytic Cracking Tower§r and the §3Electric Arc Furnace§r.

# Quest: Catalytic Cracking Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOw.name=Catalytic Cracking Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOw.desc=The §3Catalytic Cracking Tower§r is a large oil processing multiblock machine which produces many fluids, such as §bAromatic Hydrocarbons§r used for §6Bakelite§r.

# Quest: Desh Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPA.name=Desh Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPA.desc=An upgraded version of the §3Anvil§r, [T3], which unlocks additional recipes.%n%nAlternatively, the §3Desh Anvil§r can be skipped by making a §3Ferrouranium Anvil§r, [T4], from scavanged §e§r§6Uranium-238§r found in structures.

# Quest: Industrial Boiler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPw.name=Industrial Boiler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPw.desc=The §3Industrial Boiler§r is an upgraded version of the Boiler which has a higher capacity of held liquid. Additionally, it doesnt explode.

# Quest: Rubber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQA.name=Rubber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQA.desc=§6Rubber§r is an essential material used in many crafting recipes. It is created in a §3Chemical Plant§r with §bUnsaturated Hydrocarbons§r obtained from a §3Catalytic Cracking Tower§r.%n%n§6Latex§r is a rubber alternative which can be used in some recipes instead of normal rubber. It can be created early on using a §3Burner Press§r by processing dandelions or jungle wood.%n%n§2In NTM: Space cracked oil is required to obtain the first piece of rubber.

# Quest: Bakelite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQQ.name=Bakelite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQQ.desc=§6Bakelite§r is an alternative to Polymer and can be used for the same recipes. Since it doesnt require any §6Coal Powder§r or §6Fluorite§r to be made, it is easier and more convenient to automate than §6Polymer§r.

# Quest: Desh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQg.name=Desh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQg.desc=§6Desh§r is an alloy made up of 9 rare earth metals to make its blend form, which is solidified and refined using §bMercury§r and §bLight oil§r in the §3Chemical Plant§r. Desh is an almost unbreakable material and as such its tools have infinite durability. %n%n§a§2Desh can also be made using DeshReady™ in a Rotary Furnace, or later on, in an Ore Acidizer.§r%n%nMercury at this stage of the game can be obtained from centrifuging §eRedstone Ore§r or putting §eCinnabar§r in a §3Combination Oven§r. Large cinnabar veins can be found as depth ore.%n%nLater on, mercury can be obtained from processing §bOre Slop§r or §bVitriol§r in an §3Electrolyzer§r.

# Quest: Industrial Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARA.name=Industrial Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARA.desc=The §3Industrial Steam Turbine§r is a multiblock machine that is a much larger and more powerful version of the regular §3Steam Turbine§r. It has an efficiency of §e100%%§r and energy output slowly ramps up as §bSteam§r is supplied and slowly goes down as steam cuts out.

# Quest: Coker Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARQ.name=Coker Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARQ.desc=The §3Coker Unit§r is a machine that turns oil products into §6Petroleum Coke§r, which is the same to the other kinds of coke, aswell as additional fluids as byproducts. The coker unit will require an external heat source in order to function, similar to the §3Crucible§r.%n%n§2§r§2Alongside the §2§r§2§r§2Electric Arc Furnace, the coker unit is one of the most polluting machines of the mod. It spreads 20 soot per second, making it a dangerous machine to use next to a glyphid nest.

# Quest: Auxilary Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASA.name=Auxilary Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASA.desc=The §3Auxiliary Cooling Tower§r is a larger version of the Steam Condenser able to process up to 50 mb/t of §bLow-Pressure Steam§r.

# Quest: Refinery Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASw.name=Refinery Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASw.desc=Oil products can be combusted or burnt to produce massive amounts of energy.%n%nThe §3Industrial Combustion Engine§r combusts fuels, such as §bHeating Oil§r or §bDiesel§r to produce power. Various piston sets exist, which are needed for the engine to work, each one giving its own efficiency bonuses to fuel grades.%n%nThe §4§3Turbofan§r is the best place to use aviation type fuels, such as §bKerosene§r, as it provides §e100%%§r power efficiency. Be careful not to stand infront of it while its operational!%n%nThe §3Combined Cycle Gas Turbine§r is the only generator that can burn gaseous fuels at §e100%%§r efficiency. The CCGT uses §3§bEngine Lubricant§r, and produces §bDense Steam§r.%n%nThe §3Flare Stack§r is used for burning gasses such as §bUnsaturated Hydrocarbons§r for power, aswell as dealing with excess fluids.%n%nThe §3Fluid Burner§r is a much more efficient way of producing power from gases. Place a §3Boiler§r ontop and run the §bSteam§r through a turbine to generate power.%n%nConsider installing a §6Muffler§r on some of these machines as they are very loud. Shift-Click on a machine while holding a Muffler to apply.

# Quest: Pumpjack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATg.name=Pumpjack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATg.desc=The §3Pumpjack§r is a more efficient §3Oil Derrick§r which extracts 750mb of §bCrude Oil§r and a random amount of §bNatural Gas§r between 50 and 250mb in a 1.25 second cycle. It depletes a single block of a deposit after extracting a random number of cycles of oil that is on average twice as large compared to the derrick.%n%nIn total, this means that the pumpjack is on average 3x as efficient at extracting oil and 3x as fast at doing so while producing the same amount of natural gas as the derrick.

# Quest: Ore Acidizer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATw.name=Ore Acidizer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATw.desc=The §3Ore Acidizer§r is a useful machine, used for processing various items for utility, ore multiplication, and more. It is powered by electricity and requires various solvents depending on the item. The acidizer is quite the power hungry machine, consuming §e20kHE/s§r. %n%n

# Quest: Hydraulic Fracking Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUQ.name=Hydraulic Fracking Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUQ.desc=The §3Hydraulic Fracking Tower§r is used to extract infinite oil from a §eBedrock Oil Deposit§r. To operate, the machine needs §bFracking Solution§r. During its operation, the surrounding environment will sustain considerable damage. §6Oily Dirt§r and §6Oily Sand§r can be used to create §6Arsenic§r, a substitute of §6Bismuth§r.%n%nOperating the hydraulic fracking tower will consume §e100kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUg.name=Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUg.desc=The §6§3Centrifuge§r allows for the seperation of ores, giving back more items than the usual mining method. It also seperates items into their respective items. Additionally, they are used in processing §e§6Bedrock Ores§r.%n%nOperating the centrifuge will consume §e4kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Electric Groundwater Pump
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUw.name=Electric Groundwater Pump
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUw.desc=The §3Electric Groundpump§r can be used to quickly generate §bWater§r, making it very useful later on for filling large §3Tanks§r and reactors. The pump requires a 3x3 cube of dirt directly beneath it and must be below Y:70, otherwise it won't work.

# Quest: Industrial Solidification Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVw.name=Industrial Solidification Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVw.desc=The §3Industrial Solidification Machine§r is a general use machine for the solidification of various fluids.

# Quest: Industrial Liquification Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWA.name=Industrial Liquification Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWA.desc=The §3Industrial Liquification Machine§r is a general use machine for the liquifying various items. It becomes very useful for cobblestone generation, and thus §6Silicon§r automation.

# Quest: Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXg.name=Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXg.desc=§3Tanks§r and §3Barrels§r are useful storage devices that can hold various fluids in various amounts. Each tank and barrel supports holding different types of corrosive, hot, or exotic fluids, and knowing which ones can hold your desired fluids can be vital to your fluid processing and storage facilities.%n%nTanks can hold up to 256,000mb of fluids, while a Steel Barrel can hold 16,000.%n%n§4§2Tanks cant hold highly Antimatter and Corrosive fluids and as such a Big-Ass Tank 9000 or a Magnetic Tank is needed respectively.

# Quest: Geiger Counter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXw.name=Geiger Counter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXw.desc=The §6Geiger counter§r is a device used to measure §eRAD/s§r, in order to inform the player of any eventual radiation. It is an upgrade to the §6Dosimeter§r. It can measure three different types of radiation, those types being chunk radiation, environmental radiation and player contamination.%n%nIt can be used in one of two forms, either as a hand-held item or in its block form.%n%nHolding it in the inventory will show a meter on the bottom left of the screen, and right clicking while holding it will send a message in chat showing the various doses of radiation.%n%nIt will also click whenever it reads any kind of radiation, a signature function of any dosimeter.

# Quest: Survey Scanner
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYA.name=Survey Scanner
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYA.desc=The §6Survey Scanner§r is a handheld device that will point out underground resourse deposits, such as §eDepth Rock§r and §eBedrock Ores§r.

# Quest: Launch Pad
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAaw.name=Launch Pad
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAaw.desc=The §3Launch Pad§r is the main launch table for most missiles. Although it is the earliest available, missiles must first be erected before launch, resulting in a small delay.%n%nThe §3Silo Launch Pad§r is a miniaturized version of the launch pad. It can launch every generic missile with a delay of only 5 seconds. A rusted variant can be found in the naturally-occurring silo structure, holding the damaged Doomsday Missile.

# Quest: Transport Drones
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAdg.name=Transport Drones
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAdg.desc=§3Transport Drones§r are flying machines which will transport items and fluids between different containers. The drones require no power, and can transport both up and down. §3Waypoints§r can be used to make a better path for the transport drones to move around.

# Quest: Tantalum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiw.name=Tantalum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiw.desc=§6§6Tantalum§r is a material needed for the creation of some items, most importantly §6Capacitor Boards§r. Tantalum Polycrystal production requires §6Coltan§r which can be located by the use of a §6Coltass§r. Tantalum can be obtained from using §bHigh-Performance Solvent§r on §eHeavy Metal Bedrock Ore§r.%n%n§2Coltan Processing at its early stage can provide Niobium needed for Catalytic Cracking Towers.

# Quest: Electrolysis Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAzA.name=Electrolysis Machine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAzA.desc=The §3Electrolysis Machine§r enables the separating of elements from fluids and the advanced processing of ores, making it an important machine in ore processing. Operating the machine consumes §e200kHE/s§r.%n%nThe electrolysis machine has 2 functions: one for the separation of fluids and one for ore processing.%n%nIn the first mode, the machine will take in a compatible fluid and separate it into 2 other fluids.%n%nIn the second mode, it will require §bNitric Acid§r and will process any kind of ore-derived crystal, allowing the maximum yield of the ore. There are 2 outputs, for the molten main product the outlet marked green and the secondary the one marked red, plus a byproduct kept in its item form. The outlets follow the same mechanics as the §3Crucible§r.%n%n§2Consider installing a Power Saving upgrade above level 2 on the electrolysis machine as it will significantly reduce the power consumption with only a minimal speed penalty.

# Quest: Microchip
betterquesting.quest.Lc9HRIDwRZa0u-M3Ze6ZiQ.name=Microchip
betterquesting.quest.Lc9HRIDwRZa0u-M3Ze6ZiQ.desc=§6Microchips§r are one of the most important components of future circuits and will be used in bulk throughout progression.

# Quest: Precision Assembler
betterquesting.quest.RACFotYCSpG7BihFhonkCA.name=Precision Assembler
betterquesting.quest.RACFotYCSpG7BihFhonkCA.desc=The §3Precision Assembler§r is a machine which can produce §6Blueprints§r. Due to the recipes having a low success rate, automation of the ingredient is recommended.%n%nPufferfish can be obtained from throwing §6Fishing Dynamite§r in water.

# Quest: Powered Drill
betterquesting.quest.UWNifpoeQfypMwfGniM40w.name=Powered Drill
betterquesting.quest.UWNifpoeQfypMwfGniM40w.desc=The §6Powered Drill§r is a modular mining device which can make resourse gathering and excavation much faster than normal pickaxes. %n%nVarious modifications can be attached in the §3Weapon Modification Table§r, such as new drillbits for a larger mining radious or even new engines, which let it run on electricity.

# Quest: Redstone Fluid Overflow
betterquesting.quest.ZTrtIRiyRO2J5jHQ4sroaQ.name=Redstone Fluid Overflow
betterquesting.quest.ZTrtIRiyRO2J5jHQ4sroaQ.desc=§6§6§3Redstone-Over Radio§r in combination with a §3Redstone Fluid Valve§r can be used to detect when a tank is starting to fill up, and release the insides. This is useful for having buffers without having all the fluids being wasted.%n%n§2Here is an exmaple of a tank that will only output fluid once its full:§r%n%nFirstly, place a §6ROR Transmitter§r on one port of the tank, provide an ID and enable Polling.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Fluid1.png[/img]%n%nAfter that, place a §6ROR Logic Receiver§r next to the fluid valve and input the desired settings. Make sure that your signal is >= of your desired buffer. One redstone level equals to 16k mb.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Fluid2.png[/img]%n%nA §3Fluid Control Pump§r can also be used to limit throughput of fluids and to also add priorities.

# Quest: Redstone-Over-Radio Logic
betterquesting.quest.gNS_yBDSS7uk2N7wr9PuYw.name=Redstone-Over-Radio Logic
betterquesting.quest.gNS_yBDSS7uk2N7wr9PuYw.desc=Redstone-Over-Radio, as its name suggests, is used to wirelessly transmit redstone signals. There are various types of components, all of which being very useful for precise automation.

# Quest: Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.l6zSmdfhSw6aTqiJsNDiHg.name=Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.l6zSmdfhSw6aTqiJsNDiHg.desc=The §6Jetpack§r can be used to travel upwards. It can be upgraded to unlock additional abilities, and can be equiped as an armor modification.

# Quest: Fiberglass
betterquesting.quest.mBnOQ4Z5TBiM29bD4GXBvQ.name=Fiberglass
betterquesting.quest.mBnOQ4Z5TBiM29bD4GXBvQ.desc=Sand in an §3Ore Acidizer§r can be turned into §6Fiberglass§r, which provides more than §e4x§r the amount of §6Silicon§r in an §3Arc Furnace§r. Additionally, it provides a great recipe for insulators.

# Quest: Weapon Steel
betterquesting.quest.xADm9gLETmCgiS3amOTUcQ.name=Weapon Steel
betterquesting.quest.xADm9gLETmCgiS3amOTUcQ.desc=§6Weapon steel§r is a steel alloy made by further refining steel in a §3Rotary Furnace§r. As its name implies, it is used in the crafting of weapons and ammunition. It is the next tier of weapons grade alloy after §6Gunmetal§r.

# Quest: Arc Furnace ROR Automation
betterquesting.quest.xqZqIvJgRa25Gj5Qr25Wcg.name=Arc Furnace ROR Automation
betterquesting.quest.xqZqIvJgRa25Gj5Qr25Wcg.desc=§2This quest serves as a guide on how to precisely input items in an arc furnace as not to waste electrode durability.§r%n%nAssuming no upgrades are inserted in the §3Arc Furnace§r, there are exactly 20 slots available for items. To start, route all input items into a §3Conveyor Boxer§r which will send items into a §3Conveyor Unboxer§r. Adding speed ejection and stack ejection upgrades to the unboxer is highly recommended as so the items are inputed fast enough.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_ARC1.png[/img]%n%nPlace a §3Redstone-Over-Radio Item Counter§r on one side of the boxer, set the item filter and give it an ID.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_ARC2.png[/img]%n%nThen place a Redstone-Over-Radio Logic Receiver, give it the correct ID, and set it to emit redstone when item count is 20.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_ARC3.png[/img]%n%nMake sure that the boxer has its mode set to redstone.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_ARC4.png[/img]

# Quest: Mining Laser
betterquesting.quest.zYS6AlyFSuuMUErAJqPcTg.name=Mining Laser
betterquesting.quest.zYS6AlyFSuuMUErAJqPcTg.desc=The §3Mining Laser§r is a laser drill which can be used to quickly dig large areas. It has a §e100MHE§r internal power buffer and a 64,000mB internal §bCrude Oil§r buffer. Its default radius is 3, which can be increased by the use of an effectiveness upgrade. It can also be equiped with various upgrades to unlock new functions such as shredding or voiding.


## Quest Line: NTM: Reactors
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAg.name=NTM: Reactors
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAg.desc=As energy needs increase, more powerful energy sources will be needed. This chapter covers Nuclear Reactors aswell as other advanced machines needed to produce ever stronger materials.

# Quest: Gas Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.2JMb-t2STTKM5sxV5Z7WOQ.name=Gas Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.2JMb-t2STTKM5sxV5Z7WOQ.desc=The §3Gas Centrifuge§r is used to centrifuge §bUranium/Plutonium Hexafluoride§r to obtain enriched fuel for bombs and reactor fuel.%n%nTwo gas centrifuges in a row will yield §6Uranium-238§r and §6Uranium Fuel§r used in reactors. The uranium hexafluoride processing line does not consume the §6Sulfur§r and §6Fluorite§r, so loops are recommended.%n%nThe §6Gas Centrifuge Overclocking Upgrade§r is needed to obtain §6Uranium-235§r. Four gas centrifuges will have to be placed in a row and the upgrade on the last of them to obtain uranium-235 nuggets.%n%n[F1] For more information.%n

# Quest: Ferrouranium
betterquesting.quest.4jgH-_iMTDOer91Gj2FXiQ.name=Ferrouranium
betterquesting.quest.4jgH-_iMTDOer91Gj2FXiQ.desc=§6Ferrouranium§r is an alloy of §6Uranium-238§r and §6Steel§r.

# Quest: Tungsten Carbide
betterquesting.quest.6GYfg5blTqC0-zrnYjON8w.name=Tungsten Carbide
betterquesting.quest.6GYfg5blTqC0-zrnYjON8w.desc=§6Tungsten Carbide§r is an alloy made from §6Tungsten§r and §bSyngas§r in a §3Pyrolysis Oven§r. It is mainly used in crafting neutron reflectors for reactors and nukes.

# Quest: Nuclear Fuel Processing
betterquesting.quest.7rFMNl3iSCOD-dpsKLAANQ.name=Nuclear Fuel Processing
betterquesting.quest.7rFMNl3iSCOD-dpsKLAANQ.desc=With the §3Spent Fuel Pool Drum§r to cool down §3ZIRNOX§r or §3PWR§r depleted nuclear fuel and the §3PUREX§r to further process them, many new materials are now available.

# Quest: Fusion Reactor
betterquesting.quest.8DXv-b9sRxalmY8yovSQuw.name=Fusion Reactor
betterquesting.quest.8DXv-b9sRxalmY8yovSQuw.desc=The §3Fusion Reactor§r is a large, expensive, and advanced reactor type that runs by fusing various plasma types to generate heat.%n%nThe main part of the fusion reactor, the §3"Torus"§r, features four connecting ports for external components. It requires electricity and §bPerfluoromethyl§r cooling to operate.%n%nThe §3Klystron§r is the main power source of the fusion reactor, which uses electricity and compressed air, to generate input energy, §eKyU§r, for the connected torus. It will throttle if the buffered electricity or compressed air falls below §e50%%§r, and if it falls below the torus' required input level, the plasma will extinguish.%n%nThe different plasma types also generate different useful byproducts and differing levels of neutron flux for breeding bulk quantities of materials, such as §6Lithium§r into §6Tritium§r.%n%nWelding the coils will require a §6Blowtorch§r or an §6Acetylene Welding Torch§r.%n%nMore information can be found below:%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Fusion_Reactor[/url]%n%n§2For the additional components and power generation methods, please check out the two quests below.§r%n%n§2Multiple fusion reactors will be required soon so it is recommended that Bedrock Ore Processing and Oil Refinement is automated.§r

# Quest: Large Factory Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.8XHLo-wQRN28gu4AwCtHVQ.name=Large Factory Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.8XHLo-wQRN28gu4AwCtHVQ.desc=The §3Chemical Factory§r is a large version of the §3Chemical Plant§r, capable of performing 4 recipes in parallel. It has double the speed of the chemical plant but consumes twice as much power. Additionally, it consumes §bWater§r as a coolant, and produces §bLow-Pressure Steam§r, so a closed water cycle is recommended.%n%nThe §3Assembly Factory§r is a large version of the §3Assembly Machine§r, capable of performing 4 recipes in parallel. It functions the same as the chemical factory.

# Quest: Chlorophyte
betterquesting.quest.8oOJm62fRmKMu-HJni7Pwg.name=Chlorophyte
betterquesting.quest.8oOJm62fRmKMu-HJni7Pwg.desc=§6Chlorophyte§r is a product of fusion and is used in the §3DFC§r and §6Digamma Particle§r.

# Quest: Starmetal Pickaxe
betterquesting.quest.8sIzBzykSPqskvhCp-Tsmw.name=Starmetal Pickaxe
betterquesting.quest.8sIzBzykSPqskvhCp-Tsmw.desc=The §6Starmetal Pickaxe§r is used as a crafting component for the §6Molten§r and §6Bismuth Pickaxes§r, both being unbreakable and having a lot of abilities. Additionally, both can be used to mine §eDepth Rock§r.%n

# Quest: Cadmium
betterquesting.quest.9BjXTD5CSTOQ-_OroVdJmg.name=Cadmium
betterquesting.quest.9BjXTD5CSTOQ-_OroVdJmg.desc=§6Cadmium§r is a material needed to make §6Cadmium Stee§rl, which is a substitute of §6Technetium Steel§r.%n%nCadmium can be obtained by smelting cadmium powder, which can be obtained acidizing 10 §6Mustard Willow leaves§r with 250mB of §bHigh-Perfomance Solvent§r in the §3Ore Acidizer§r.%n%nThe mustard willow is a plant that can be found near §eBedrock Oil Deposits§r. When it's fully matured, the main item can be obtained, that being the mustard willow leaf.

# Quest: High-Power Steam Condenser
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0Q.name=High-Power Steam Condenser
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0Q.desc=The §3High-Power Steam Condenser§r is the a steam condenser which runs on electricity. It processes up to 60 mB/t of §bLow-Pressure Steam§r.

# Quest: Leviathan Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA1Q.name=Leviathan Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA1Q.desc=The §3Leviathan Steam Turbine§r is a massive turbine capable of processing gargantuan amounts of §bSteam§r at once, only hindered by the fluid system's transfer rate. It is significantly more powerful than even the §3Industrial Steam Turbine§r in terms of raw steam processing power. This turbine runs on §e85%%§r Efficiency, so it is recommended that only 1-2 are used for very large reactors.

# Quest: RBMK
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA.name=RBMK
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA.desc=The §3RBMK§r is a modular boiling-water type nuclear fission reactor which consists entirely of concrete columns. Each of these columns is either blank or has a specific function that it performs such as holding fuel rods, moderating neutrons, or storing §bWater§r to be boiled into §bSteam§r. Each column will also exchange heat with the column next to it such that temperature differences between columns will gradually equalize within the reactor. If any column reaches §e1500°C§r, the reactor will explode incredibly violently, spraying scrap and immensely radioactive material in every direction.%n%nDue to the complex and expansive nature of the RBMK, it is highly recommend that the wiki is checked out as it provides more information.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/RBMK[/url]%n%n§2This quest provides an optional retrieval task for a cheap and safe RBMK design which can produce High-Performance Solvent§r §2without cooling. Simply Place the RBMK Irradiation Channel next to the RBMK Fuel Rod, apply the covers on the collumns and surround them with a solid block.

# Quest: Technetium/Cadmium Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABg.name=Technetium/Cadmium Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABg.desc=§6Technetium/Cadmium Steel§r is a steel based alloy mixed with technetium-99/Cadmium which has extreme corrosion resistance. It is frequently used in the late-game and acts as one of the main material gates of the §3Fusion§r and §3Watz§r powerplant.

# Quest: PWR
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACg.name=PWR
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACg.desc=The §2§3PWR§r is a modular fission reactor. It is more limited than the §3RBMK§r in terms of capability and fuel types but it is much safer and easier to use due to it melting down more gently and being far more stable in its operation.%n%nDue to the complex and expansive nature of the PWR, it is highly recommend that the wiki is checked out as it provides more information.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/PWR[/url]%n%n§2This quest demands the most essential parts of a PWR, and does not represent the amount needed for a functioning reactor. There are also many other types of PWR Components that can be used.

# Quest: Reformate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADQ.name=Reformate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADQ.desc=§bReformate§r is a product of §bCrude Oil§r obtained via a §3Vacuum Refinery§r or from processing §bNaptha§r in a §3Hydrotreater§r.%n%n§2This step can be skipped if making Jet Fuel and BTX using a Hydrotreater.%n

# Quest: Starmetal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJw.name=Starmetal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJw.desc=§6Starmetal§r is a unique alloy made from combining §6Saturnite§r with §6Meteorite Powder§r in a §3Blast Furnace§r.

# Quest: Versatile Integrated Circuit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKA.name=Versatile Integrated Circuit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKA.desc=The §6Versatile Integrated Circuit§r is the first circuit to use §6Bismuth/Arsenic§r. It is used in more advanced machines such as the §3Vacuum Refinery§r and is one of the main components of §6Versatile Circuit Boards§r.

# Quest: Liquidator Medal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALQ.name=Liquidator Medal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALQ.desc=Incase of an §3RBMK§r meltdown, §6Fuel Chunks§r will be thrown near the reactor. The §6Liquidator Medal§r is an armor modification which passively reduces radiation, making it very useful when handling radioactive items or venturing into irradiated areas.

# Quest: Versatile Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMA.name=Versatile Circuit Board
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMA.desc=The §6Versatile Circuit Board§r is the final tier of circuit board, requiring §6Bismuth/Arsenic§r and §6Hard Plastic/PVC Bars§r.  As well as this, it is by far the most expensive circuit board, requiring nearly 55 insulators to craft a single one. Used rarely but in small amounts in advanced machines like the §3Fusion Reactor§r and in large amounts in components for the §3ICF Reactor§r.

# Quest: Hard Plastic/PVC Bars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANA.name=Hard Plastic/PVC Bars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANA.desc=§6Hard Plastic/PVC Bars§r are very durable plastics needed for many late game recipes. %n%n§2Both can be used in the same recipes.

# Quest: Pyrolysis Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANg.name=Pyrolysis Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANg.desc=The §3Pyrolysis Oven§r is a mid-to-late game oil processing machine that allows easier production pf §6Crystalline Fullerite§r, which is needed in bulk for late-game machines onwards. %n%nIt can process an item with an optional fluid to produce another item and/or fluid. Functionally, it works similar to the §3Combination Oven§r, mostly in bedrock ore processing.%nIts main use however is in production of §6Fullerene§r, as it can turn §6Tar§r into §6Fine Soot§r, eliminating the RNG of a §3Smokestack§r.%n%nOperating the pyrolysis oven will consume §e200kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Reformate Gas
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPg.name=Reformate Gas
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPg.desc=§bReformate Gas§r is used in welding very durable materials, aswell as used in making §6Saturnite§r.

# Quest: FEL and SILEX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQw.name=FEL and SILEX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAQw.desc=The §3FEL§r or Free Electron Laser is a large multiblock utilized with the SILEX to produce various laser wavelengths needed for all SILEX recipes.%n%nA single FEL can power up to 5 SILEX'es. In order to stop the laser any concrete block can be in the its path.%n%nThe lower the wavelength of the crystal, the faster recipes will be completed.%n%nThe §6§3SILEX§r is a machine that separates isotopes and elements from compounds or other materials via the SILEX (Separation of Isotopes by Laser Exitation) process. It allows for easier enrichment of §6Uranium§r, §6Plutonium§r, and §6Australium§r.%n%nThe SILEX can also process §6Lapis Lazuli§r into §6Sulfur§r, §6Aluminium§r, and most importantly §6Cobalt§r. It can use §bHydrogen Peroxide§r to liquify any material to be processed, the material may even be in a powder state. The processed items come out into the right side collection of slots.%n%nThe SILEX must be placed at least 2 blocks away from activated FEL laser, or else its going to melt.

# Quest: Saturnite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASQ.name=Saturnite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASQ.desc=§6Saturnite§r is a very durable, heat-resistant and corrosion-resistant alloy that is commonly used for making stronger gun parts. It is also used to make §6Starmetal§r and is an important component of the §3Watz§r reactor.

# Quest: Gravity Gun
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASg.name=Gravity Gun
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASg.desc=The §6Gravity Gun§r is an advanced tool which can lift and throw blocks. It is particularly useful for moving highly hazardous blocks, such as corium from a reactor meltdown, or throwing explosives.%n%n§T§2The gravity gun can be supercharged in a Fusion Reactor Breeding Chamber, further increasing its range and power.§r

# Quest: Schrabidium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVg.name=Schrabidium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVg.desc=§6Schrabidium§r is a dangerous material, but one which is needed for the creation of other items, such as §6Magnetized Tungsten§r and §6Ferric Schrabidate§r. It also makes for great reactor fuel. It can be created from exposing uranium ore to radiation using either a nuclear weapon or, more easily, by exploding radioactive barrels found in the abandoned nuclear powerplants in deserts.%n%n§2When holding Schrabidium, the player will receive the blindness effect, so it is recommended that a Suit which provides protection from both Bright Lights and Radiation is used.

# Quest: Advanced Oil Processing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWw.name=Advanced Oil Processing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWw.desc=The §3Catalytic Reformer§r is an optional late-game oil processing machine. It converts certain oil products into more valuable ones.%n%nThe §3Hydrotreater§r is another optional late-game oil processing machine that allows for easier production of §bSour Gas§r, which can also turn §bCrude Oil§r into §bDesulfurized crude Oil§r. %n%n§2The Hydrotreater requires pressurized Liquid Hydrogen in all its recipes, requiring the use of a Compressor.

# Quest: Soyuz-FG
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAZw.name=Soyuz-FG
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAZw.desc=The §3Soyuz-FG Rocket§r is an immensely powerful Soviet rocket that is the primary launch vehicle for all satellites. The rocket must be launched from a suitably large mount - in this case, the §3Soyuz Launch Platform§r.%n%nIt requires 128,000mB of §bKerosene§r and §bLiquid Oxygen§r to be launched as well as §e750kHE§r of power. Pressing the launch button starts a 30 second countdown. After the countdown has completed, the Soyuz will launch.%n%nThe Soyuz can, alongside its primary ability to deliver any satellite to orbit, also be set to a cargo mode, in which it can deliver any provided cargo to a distant spot across the world. Obviously, this is an incredibly expensive way to transport goods, and currently doesn't provide much utility.%n%n§2Blueprints can be found in structures, purchased through Bobmazon or made in a Precision Assembler.%n

# Quest: Ferrouranium Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbw.name=Ferrouranium Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbw.desc=An upgraded version of the §3Anvil§r, [T4], which unlocks additional recipes.

# Quest: Neutrino Lens
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcA.name=Neutrino Lens
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcA.desc=The §6Neutrino Lens§r is an armor modification which can detect and highlight special blocks, such as §eBedrock Ore deposits§r, the §6Pink Log§r and §6Alexandrite§r. %n%nFor the lens to work, it must first be linked to a §6Depth-Resource Scanning Module Satellite§r and then inserted into an armor piece using the §3Armor Modification Table§r.%n%n§2The HUD key has to be activated for it to work.

# Quest: ZIRNOX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcg.name=ZIRNOX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcg.desc=The §3ZIRNOX§r is the first and cheapest nuclear reactor that one can make. Unlike the §3PWR§r and §3RBMK§r, it is a fully assembled reactor which requires §bWater§r and §bCarbon Dioxide§r to operate.%n%nDue to the low amount of steam the ZIRNOX makes, one can use the singleblock §3Steam Turbines§r, at the cost of §e85%%§r efficiency, and a single §3Steam Condenser§r on lower power fuels. Thus, 24 §6Natural Uranium Fuel Rods§r using 14kmB of carbon dioxide will yield a power output of around §e160kHE/s§r.

# Quest: Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAdQ.name=Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAdQ.desc=The §3Cooling Tower§r is a larger version of the §3Auxiliary Cooling Tower§r§r, able to process up to 500 mB/t of §bLow-Pressure Steam§r.

# Quest: Ionized Particles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeA.name=Ionized Particles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeA.desc=§6Ionized Particles§r are the main product of the §3Fusion Reactor§r and are used in making §6Ferric Scrabidate§r, aswell as some particle capsules needed in the §3Particle Accelerator§r.%n%n§2Ionized Particles can be infinitely produced by utilizing Ionic Gel.

# Quest: HEV Mark IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhA.name=HEV Mark IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhA.desc=The §6HEV Mark IV§r is a strong electric armor set, with the intent of keeping the user safe primarely from dangerous hazards, such as high levels of radiation, fire, certain air particles and more. The suit comes equiped with an §6Geiger Counter§r and custom hud.

# Quest: Bismuth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhw.name=Bismuth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhw.desc=§6Bismuth§r is an important material needed in many advanced crafting recipes. Bismuth can be obtained from either §3RBMK§r fuel depletion and processing though a §3FEL§r and §3SILEX§r, or from bedrock ore processing using §bHigh-Performance Solvent§r. %n%n§6Arsenic§r will require an additional §bOre Acidizer§r aswell as access to high-performance solvent.%n%n§2Due to the lack of bismuth bedrock ore available on earth and the amount of time it takes to process RBMK fuels, it is recommended that some arsenic is used instead of bismuth.

# Quest: Research and Breeding Reactor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiA.name=Research and Breeding Reactor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiA.desc=The §3Research Reactor§r is a non-power reactor intended for burning fuel efficiently and acting as a neutron source for §3Breeding Reactor§ss§r. It has to be submerged in §bWater§r to cool since it does not have the active cooling of a typical power reactor. A §6Ra226Be§r or §6Pu238Be§r neutron source plate is needed to begin the reaction, and then can be removed. It explodes at exactly §e1,000°C§r, so caution is advised when using strong fuels and several breeders simultaneously.%n%nA §3Reactor Remote Control§  Block§r%nand a §6Reactor Remote Sensor§r can be used to activate and monitor the reactor from a distance.%n%nThe Breeding Reactor breeds isotopes of elements into heavier forms using the neutron flux of an adjacent Research Reactor. When the reactor is operating, rays of green-ish "lightning" emitted from the center rod of the model can be seen going to the outer rods from the glass observation window.

# Quest: Welded Technetium/Cadmium Steel Plate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAjg.name=Welded Technetium/Cadmium Steel Plate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAjg.desc=The §6Welded Technetium/Cadmium Steel Plate§r is the welded varient of the cast technetium/cadmium steel plate and is used in some recipes that require strong materials. %n%n§2Make sure to have good energy generation and storage infrastructure as each plate costs 1.2 Billion HE.

# Quest: Big-Ass Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAjw.name=Big-Ass Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAjw.desc=The §3Big-Ass Tank§r is the largest fluid storage container, capable of storing 16000000mB of fluids, aswell as being able to hold strongly corrosive fluids.%n%n§2Must be placed on solid ground or else it will tilt.§r

# Quest: Heavy Magnetic Storage Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAkA.name=Heavy Magnetic Storage Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAkA.desc=The §3Heavy Magnetic Storage Tank§r is a large version of the §3Magnetic Antimatter Container§r. It will be particularly useful when making §6Gerald§r, as he will need very large quantities of §bStellar Flux§r.

# Quest: Vacuum Refinery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAkw.name=Vacuum Refinery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAkw.desc=The §3Vacuum Refinery§r is an oil refinery which processes §bPressurized/Desulfurized Crude Oil§r into 4 liquid products. It is a good way to make §bHigh-Performance Solvent§r by using §bReformate Gas§r and §bChlorine Gas§r in an §3Industrial Mixer§r.%n%n§2Compressors are needed for the oil to be inserted inside the Vacuum Refinery.

# Quest: BTX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAng.name=BTX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAng.desc=§bBTX§r is a high-grade powerful fuel which generates a lot of power when burnt. An important use of BTX is in the creation of §6Crystalline Fullerite§r and §6Hard Plastic Bars§r. BTX can be obtained from a §3Hydrotreater§r, but it is more efficient to use §bReformate§r from a §3Vacuum Refinery§r.

# Quest: Watz Powerplant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAApg.name=Watz Powerplant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAApg.desc=The §3Watz§r powerplant is a fission reactor which can produce §bPoisonous Mud§r, an important component of §6CMB Steel§r. Although the reactor is not really powerful in terms of energy output, it can be stacked ontop of eachother for increased mud and power production.%n%nIf the poisonous mud buffer reaches its maximum, the reactor will melt down and explode, irradiating a wide area around it and causing fallout to fall in a small area around it. As well as this, it will spew poisonous mud in a very wide area which will then corrode any blocks that it comes in contact with, similar to corium.

# Quest: Magnetized Tungsten
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArQ.name=Magnetized Tungsten
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArQ.desc=§6Magnetized Tungsten§r is the product of combining §6Schrabidium§r and §6Tungsten§r in a §3Blast Furnace§r. It can also be rarely dropped by cybercrabs in §eMeteorite Dungeons§r.

# Quest: Ferric Schrabidate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuA.name=Ferric Schrabidate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuA.desc=§6Ferric Schrabidate§r is an alloy made from §6Iron§r, §6Ionized Particles§r and §6Schrabidium§r.

# Quest: Solid Mud Brick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuQ.name=Solid Mud Brick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAuQ.desc=§6Poisonous Mud§r is the byproduct of the §3Watz§r operating. This is the solidified version of it which can be used in a §3Crucible§r to create §6CMB Steel§r.

# Quest: CMB Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAug.name=CMB Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAug.desc=§6CMB Steel§r is an alloy made from §6Poisonous Mud§r and §6Magnetized Tunsten§r in a §3Crucible§r. This alloy is used in endgame machinery, such as the §3ICF§r and §3DFC§r.

# Quest: Crystalline Fullerite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAww.name=Crystalline Fullerite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAww.desc=§6Crystalline Fullerite§r is an material which is primarely used in endgame machines, such as the §3ICF§r and the §3FEnSU§r.%n%n§2It is recommended that an Effectiveness 3 upgrade is installed on the Acidizer to increase the chance of not consuming the Fullerene, as fullerite can be expensive to produce large quantities.

# Quest: High-Performance Solvent
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABPQ.name=High-Performance Solvent
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABPQ.desc=§bHigh-Performance Solvent§r is a solvent which is used in an §3Ore Acidizer§r to further increase the products of bedrock ores, aswell as other recipes. It can be created from §bReformate Gas§r, from a §3Vacuum Refinery§r, and §bChlorine§r in an §3Industrial Mixer§r or be obtained from an §3RBMK§r Irradiation Channel.%n%nTo transport High-Performance Solvent by hand, a §6Hazardous Material Tank§r is needed.%n%n§2High-Performance Solvent made from an RBMK irradiation channel requires an ore acidizer.%n

# Quest: Radiation-Powered Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABeA.name=Radiation-Powered Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABeA.desc=The §3Radiation-Powered Engine§r turns nuclear waste into decayed waste while also making energy in the process and giving guaranteed consistent decay times.%n%n§2Blueprints can be found in structures, purchased from Bobmazon or made in a Precision Assembler.

# Quest: Uranium-238
betterquesting.quest.CYtQLn_VSx2QTnLEwpMGOw.name=Uranium-238
betterquesting.quest.CYtQLn_VSx2QTnLEwpMGOw.desc=§6Uranium-238§r is the most common uranium isotope in the game. %n%nThis material has many uses, some of which are: §6Ferrouranium§r, MOX fuel, depleted uranium ammunition, absorber Pellets for the §3Watz§r powerplant and can also be turned into §6Schrabidium§r later on in the §3Exposure Chamber§r.

# Quest: PWR powered Steel Furnace
betterquesting.quest.E6sLN7FkSrqAHohBC1W7gQ.name=PWR powered Steel Furnace
betterquesting.quest.E6sLN7FkSrqAHohBC1W7gQ.desc=Instead of using the §bHot Coolant§r for power, one can use it to make the §3Steel Furnace§r go at ludicrous speeds.

# Quest: Additional Fusion Attachments
betterquesting.quest.JpsvBP1yQsu-XtkeZegA6A.name=Additional Fusion Attachments
betterquesting.quest.JpsvBP1yQsu-XtkeZegA6A.desc=The §3Fusion Reactor Coupler§r turns outgoing plasma energy from a torus into usable §eKyE§r which can then be used to power another torus. Some fuel combinations require this, as the minimum §eKyE§r energy needed to ignite the plasma exceeds what four §3Klystrons§r could deliver.%n%nThe §3Fusion Reactor Breeding Chamber§r uses neutron flux from a torus to in order to process materials. It can perform any recipe from an §3RBMK irradiation channel§r, with some additional recipes aswell. The neutron flux is not affected by port sharing rules, and the output level is the same on any side.%n%nThe §3Fusion Reactor Collection Chamber§r increases the byproduct production rate by §e50%%§r.

# Quest: Plasma Forge
betterquesting.quest.LWQk4lZUTwqfXvCfPUbKXw.name=Plasma Forge
betterquesting.quest.LWQk4lZUTwqfXvCfPUbKXw.desc=The §3Plasma Forge§r is a large and advanced assembler that requires a running fusion reactor to work. It can weld plates at twice the speed of a normal welder. It does not accept upgrades, however, it can use up otherwise useless fission fragments and unstable isotopes to gain a temporary §ex4§r speed bonus with no penalty.%n%n§2With 3MTU/t plasma energy input, one can make pre-assembled fusion reactors with a discount.§r§r

# Quest: Chicago Pile Automation
betterquesting.quest.M52T9-fTRi-0j18IHSGDVg.name=Chicago Pile Automation
betterquesting.quest.M52T9-fTRi-0j18IHSGDVg.desc=§2The following quest serves as a guide on how to automate the production of fuels produced by a chicago pile.§r%n%nBegin by constructing a chicago pile in a ⊥ shape, where the two sides are for the neutron sources (item frames are in place to indicate) and the middle two are for fuel breeding. Place a conveyor going out into storage from the bottom middle graphite block.%n%nOne block above the top graphite block place an §3Inserter§r (not conveyor one) facing down one block above the top graphite block. The inserter, once given a redstone signal and a fuel rod, will place the fuel into the top drilled graphite. If the bottom drilled graphite is empty (fuel bred and exported) the inserter will move the fuel from the top drilled graphite into the bottom one, and place a new fuel rod at the top.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_CHICAGO1.png[/img]%n%nPlace a §3Redstone-Over Radio Transmitter§r on the bottom drilled graphite above the conveyor and give it an ID.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_CHICAGO2.png[/img]%n%nHead over to the inserter above and place a Redstone-Over Radio Receiver. Put the same ID as the transmitter below, set it to Custom Mapping and make it output a redstone level once it receives power from the transmitter below.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_CHICAGO3.png[/img]

# Quest: Red Key
betterquesting.quest.NB6qs0xZSHaY5Sik2IoTxg.name=Red Key
betterquesting.quest.NB6qs0xZSHaY5Sik2IoTxg.desc=The §6Red Key§r is able to open any container that requires a regular key, regardless of the pin configuration of the lock, and it is one of the only two keys capable of opening the keyhole found on strange stone, in order to open a §eRed Room§r. The key has no durability, and can be reused indefinitely.%n%n

# Quest: Fusion Power
betterquesting.quest.WS2zNdGdTnmclQfj2ARCog.name=Fusion Power
betterquesting.quest.WS2zNdGdTnmclQfj2ARCog.desc=The §3Fusion Reactor Boiler§r is simplest method of extracting power from a fusion reactor, outputting §bSuper Dense Steam§r to be run through normal turbines.%n%nDue to using plasma energy, both the MHDT and the boiler are affected by port sharing rules, meaning that having multiple connected MHTDs, or boilers, decreases the amount of energy each turbine gets, but overall increases the total amount of extracted from the torus.%n

# Quest: Desh Stamps
betterquesting.quest.Wo-Z9nSKSH2ATqZXnY3CfA.name=Desh Stamps
betterquesting.quest.Wo-Z9nSKSH2ATqZXnY3CfA.desc=§6Desh Stamps§r have infinite durability, perfect for automation.

# Quest: Fissile Materials
betterquesting.quest.X6nUcp16QUqawLXQTqFTBw.name=Fissile Materials
betterquesting.quest.X6nUcp16QUqawLXQTqFTBw.desc=With fissile materials obtained from either §3Gas Centrifuges§r or nuclear fuel processing, nuclear bombs are made available.

# Quest: RBMK Fuel Processing
betterquesting.quest.a0YRGBjSTGiD09r4LqD8EA.name=RBMK Fuel Processing
betterquesting.quest.a0YRGBjSTGiD09r4LqD8EA.desc=With the §3Nuclear Waste Disposal Drum§r to decay waste and a §3SILEX§r, §3RBMK§r nuclear fuels can be processed into many new materials.

# Quest: Nuclear Waste Disposal Drum
betterquesting.quest.eadYFbwuQTS39P9cW-D-Fw.name=Nuclear Waste Disposal Drum
betterquesting.quest.eadYFbwuQTS39P9cW-D-Fw.desc=The §3Nuclear Waste Disposal Drum§r is used to decay §3RBMK§r nuclear waste. The decayed nuclear waste can then be used with a §3FEL§r and §3SILEX§r to obtain some rare elements, such as §6Bismuth§r.%n%n§2The drum also emmits radiation when theres fuel inside it.

# Quest: PUREX
betterquesting.quest.g3S9-75wTGyQKmZaQTZl5Q.name=PUREX
betterquesting.quest.g3S9-75wTGyQKmZaQTZl5Q.desc=The §3PUREX§r is a machine that can reprocess depleted nuclear fuel into various materials. Most recipes require both §bNitric Acid§r and §bKerosene§r to function.%n%n§6Schrabidium§r can also be extracted from certain recipes, which require §bSchrabidic Acid§r. The schrabidium extracted yields double the schrabidium used to make the acid.

# Quest: Chicago Pile
betterquesting.quest.g8IVppPpTceY55PbNbceJQ.name=Chicago Pile
betterquesting.quest.g8IVppPpTceY55PbNbceJQ.desc=The §3Chicago Pile§r is a crude early-game breeding reactor meant to produce §6Plutonium§r for use as reactor fuel.%n%nA pile is composed of drilled §6Graphite§r which can hold a variety of items in it, including radioisotope rods (§6Uranium§r, §6Radium§r, §6Plutonium§r), §6Lithium rods§r, and control rods. It does not behave as a unified single block, instead each individual piece of drilled graphite interacts with each other piece in a unique way depending on the rod it contains.%n%nAfter sufficient flux, the uranium rods in the Chicago Pile will transmute into plutonium rods that can be processed in an anvil into §6Reactor Grade Plutonium§r which can be used in other reactors such as the §3ZIRNOX§r and §3RBMK§r.%n%nThe chicago pile requires a significant amount of graphite blocks, which once placed can be drilled into with the hand drill to place any rod into. %n%nThe §6Hand Drill§r can be used to drill holes into the graphite or take core samples of the uranium fuel to determine heat, depletion, and neutron flux. §6Screwdrivers§r are used to extract rods.%n%nThe Quest asks for a 3x3 Chicago Pile (without the corners) with a §6Ra226Be§r Rod in the center surrounded by Uranium Rods.

# Quest: Spent Fuel Pool Drum
betterquesting.quest.har7pEFcSRKNgIf4NgmcLA.name=Spent Fuel Pool Drum
betterquesting.quest.har7pEFcSRKNgIf4NgmcLA.desc=The §3Spent Fuel Pool Drum§r is used to cool down hot nuclear fuel rods for the §3RBMK§r, §3ZIRNOX§r and §3PWR§r. It has 12 slots.%n%nThe drum needs to have atleast one of its sides touching §bWater§r to work. The more sides that have water the faster the fuels inside will cool down.

# Quest: Technetium-99
betterquesting.quest.iJiX7wxoSBmljc9tITqIqQ.name=Technetium-99
betterquesting.quest.iJiX7wxoSBmljc9tITqIqQ.desc=§6Technetium-99§r is a common waste product from the fission of §6Uranium§r and §6Plutonium§r. It is mainly used in making §6Technetium Steel§r and §dAE2 Storage Components§r.

# Quest: Satellite Launching
betterquesting.quest.ocylWycmSd6r-mvYENYGEw.name=Satellite Launching
betterquesting.quest.ocylWycmSd6r-mvYENYGEw.desc=Satelites in NTM space can be launched from either a Souyz or a custom rocket.

# Quest: Heat Exchanging Heater
betterquesting.quest.rRJfZe74TXqpP-q2faX7bA.name=Heat Exchanging Heater
betterquesting.quest.rRJfZe74TXqpP-q2faX7bA.desc=The §4§3Heat Exchanging Heater§r is used to cool down coolants used in reactors while also genearting §eTU§r. A §3Boiler§r can be placed ontop of it to heat up other fluids, such as §bSteam§r, to be used in §3Steam Turbines§r.

# Quest: Nuclear Bombs
betterquesting.quest.sCe8OyBsQEeMrUpYXUn9Yw.name=Nuclear Bombs
betterquesting.quest.sCe8OyBsQEeMrUpYXUn9Yw.desc=With access to §6Tantalum§r for §6Control Units§r and fissile matterials, it is possible to assemble a nuclear bomb. To detonate the bomb one can use a detonator or a redstone signal.%n%nA nuclear explosion will transform ores into more valuable ones, such as §6Coal§r to §6Diamonds§r or §6Uranium§r to §6Schrabidium§r. Be prepared with radiation resistant armor before venturing into the crater.%n%nMake sure to stand behind some strong cover if you wish to see the explosion from close by.%n%n§2This quest serves as a list of components needed for various bombs. Some of these components can be mounted onto rockets that will carry the payload over large distances.

# Quest: Deuterium Extraction Tower
betterquesting.quest.teKlTYeLSNSvU4h8KGT0Ug.name=Deuterium Extraction Tower
betterquesting.quest.teKlTYeLSNSvU4h8KGT0Ug.desc=The §3Deuterium Extractor Tower§r is a much larger version of the Deuterium Extractor, making it an easy and viable way of making cheap fuel for the §b§r§3Fusion Reactor§r.%n%n§2A Ferrouranium Anvil is required.§r

# Quest: Arsenic
betterquesting.quest.tgpCNtEfScSyk-mdGhGxmQ.name=Arsenic
betterquesting.quest.tgpCNtEfScSyk-mdGhGxmQ.desc=§6Arsenic§r is a substitute of §6Bismuth§r which can be made from acidizing §6Oily Dirt§r, found near §ebedrock oil deposits§r or from the environmental damage the §3Fracking Tower§r does, with §bHigh-Performance Solvent§r.

# Quest: Helium-4
betterquesting.quest.wl8MTQpsQrG9gyaScmm2rg.name=Helium-4
betterquesting.quest.wl8MTQpsQrG9gyaScmm2rg.desc=§bHelium-4§r is a product of fusion and is mainly used in crafting §6Quantum Processing Units§r.


## Quest Line: NTM: End Game
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAw.name=NTM: End Game
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAw.desc=Delve into Impossible Physics, Quantum Computing, Magic and maybe even destroy the world.%nThis chapter is about building the most advanced machines to reach the end goal of the mod.

# Quest: ICF Fuels
betterquesting.quest.2BKf-swBTG61f8eVn9ynhw.name=ICF Fuels
betterquesting.quest.2BKf-swBTG61f8eVn9ynhw.desc=The §3ICF§r can process different combinations of fuels at different laser power levels. A cheap and renewable fuel that can be used to gather the §bStellar Flux§r needed for §6Gerald§r and make decent power is §bHelium-4 - Hydrogen§r.%n%nApplying a Muon Particle to a fuel pellet will decrease the power that is needed to run it.

# Quest: Quantum Computer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFg.name=Quantum Computer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFg.desc=The §6Quantum Computer§r is the most powerful out of any other control unit. It currently only used to build §6Gerald§r and the §3DFC§r.

# Quest: Solid State Quantum Processor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGA.name=Solid State Quantum Processor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGA.desc=The §6Solid State Quantum Processor§r is the first quantum circuit related component needed to make §6Quantum Processing Units§r and §6Quantum Computers§r.

# Quest: DNT Nanosuit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANQ.name=DNT Nanosuit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANQ.desc=The §6DNT Nanosuit§r is final goal of the mod. By crafting this armor you have reached the end of progression.%n%n§5Thanks for playing!

# Quest: DFC
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANw.name=DFC
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANw.desc=The §3DFC§r is the last reactor of the mod and as such is very expensive to craft. Apart from the DFC parts, two §6Catalysts§r are needed for the reactor to work.%n%n§2A Plasma Forge with a plasma input energy of 50MTU/t is required. Stellar Flux plasma is needed.§r%n%nIt is recommended that the wiki is checked out.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/DFC[/url]

# Quest: Quantum Processing Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbQ.name=Quantum Processing Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbQ.desc=The §6Quantum Processing Unit§r is the first quantum circuit one makes, used in the §3Particle Accelerator§r and §3ICF§r reactor.

# Quest: ICF
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAig.name=ICF
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAig.desc=The §3ICF§r reactor is a very expensive and powerful reactor, which can produce a substantial amount of energy. Apart from the multiblock itself, §3ICF Lasers§r must be constructed for the reactor to work. §bStellar Flux§r will be produced during its operation which is needed to craft §6Gerald§r. Consider making use of §bLiquid Lead§r as it is a very efficient coolant for the ICF.%n%n§2A Plasma Forge with a plasma input energy of 1MTU/t is required.§r%n%nIt is recommended that the wiki is checked out as it has built-in calculators for the laser power consumption and the amount of hot coolant it produces.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Inertial_Confinement_Fusion_Reactor[/url]

# Quest: Spark Laser Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABBA.name=Spark Laser Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABBA.desc=The §6Spark Laser Crystal§r unlocks new recipes, most importantly it is used to create §6Osmiridium§r.

# Quest: The Book of Boxcars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABBQ.name=The Book of Boxcars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABBQ.desc=The §6Book of Boxcars§r is an item which allows the crafting of many special items. The book can be found inside §eMeteorite Dungeons§r found randomly in the wilderness on extra-terrestial bodies, indicated by a black pillar, or in §eRed Rooms§r.

# Quest: Dineutronium Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABEA.name=Dineutronium Anvil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABEA.desc=An upgraded version of the §3Anvil§r, [T7], which unlocks additional recipes.

# Quest: Spark Singularity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABFQ.name=Spark Singularity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABFQ.desc=The §6Spark Singularity§r is a singularity made from combining all the types of singularities with §6Dineutronium§r.

# Quest: FEnSU
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABFg.name=FEnSU
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABFg.desc=The §3FenSU§r is the ultimate energy storage block, being able to store near unlimited amounts of energy.%n%n§2A Plasma Forge with a plasma input energy of 50MTU/t is required. Stellar Flux plasma is needed.§r

# Quest: Gerald the Construction Android
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABHw.name=Gerald the Construction Android
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABHw.desc=§6Gerald the Construction Android§r is the most powerful weapon in the mod. Using this has the side effect of setting the world on fire but also getting tektite, which contains §6Osmiridium§r.%n%nGerald is the hardest recipe of the mod requiring hundreds of thousands of items, mainly circuit related.%n%nVast quantities of §6Bismuth§r, §6Tantalum§r and §6Silicon§r are needed, so dont hold back on bedrock ore processing and parallelisation of many processes. If you havent already used §dAE2§r, it is highly recommended at this stage of the game.%n%nLaunching Gerald will result in a global firestorm that will decimate all life, including all trees and grass. Make sure to keep a backup of your world before launching him.  Gerald can also be launched in the §eNether§r or §eEnd§r.%n%n§2A Plasma Forge with a plasma input energy of 25MTU/t is required.§r §2DHC or Stellar Flux plasma is needed.§r%n%n§2Blueprints can be found in structures, purchased from Bobmazon or made in a Precision Assembler.

# Quest: Osmiridium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABIQ.name=Osmiridium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABIQ.desc=§6Osmiridium§r is the second most expensive material and is used primarely in the §3DFC§r.

# Quest: Yharonite Billet
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABKg.name=Yharonite Billet
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABKg.desc=The §6Yharonite Billet§r is created in a tungsten crate that has §6Polonium Billets§r in it while being shot from a §3DFC Emitter§r. This is the final material obtained in the mod.

# Quest: The Crucible
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABLw.name=The Crucible
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABLw.desc=The §6Crucible§r is a weapon that deals extreme amount of damage. It can be recharged inside a Tungsten Crate shot by a §3DFC Emitter§r.

# Quest: Schrabidium Hammer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABMA.name=Schrabidium Hammer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABMA.desc=The §6Schrabidium Hammer§r is the most powerful weapon in the mod, being able to one-shot everything.

# Quest: Magnetohydrodynamic Turbines
betterquesting.quest.BhhBylNPSPuvVJhPO93sdw.name=Magnetohydrodynamic Turbines
betterquesting.quest.BhhBylNPSPuvVJhPO93sdw.desc=§3Magnetohydrodynamic Turbines§r are advanced components of the fusion reactor that make electricity out of the plasma energy directly without needing additional turbines. While more expensive and requiring §bPerfluoromethyl§r cooling, they have a §e+35%%§r convertion bonus from §eTU§r to §eHE§r. In addition, the MDH turbine requires a minimum input of%n§e5MTU/t§r of plasma energy to operate normally, otherwise efficiency will be halved.

# Quest: ICF Laser Turbocharger
betterquesting.quest.hmwBFeuMQXiUrjE-WdD6-g.name=ICF Laser Turbocharger
betterquesting.quest.hmwBFeuMQXiUrjE-WdD6-g.desc=The §3ICF Laser Turbocharger§r can be placed next to §3ICF Laser Capacitors§r to increase the laser's power by a substantial amount, allowing for the §3ICF§r to run higher grade fuels.

# Quest: Balls-O-Tron
betterquesting.quest.k-HwTdGiQVmikRwAeg_fkQ.name=Balls-O-Tron
betterquesting.quest.k-HwTdGiQVmikRwAeg_fkQ.desc=Balls-O-Tron is the second boss of §dNTM§r. It can be summoned by interracting the mechanist's circle, found in the §eEnargite Temple§r which spawns in jungles, with a §6Silver Key§r, made using the Maskman Coin, or from crafting the Balls-O-Tron spawn item.%n%nDue to the outdated nature of the bosses, aswell as the RNG needed to obtain some of the items, this quest provides an alternative way of obtaining the Balls-O-Tron coin.%n%n§2This quest can be repeated.

# Quest: ICF Laser
betterquesting.quest.nqmqybchRzWn-T46-3vHmQ.name=ICF Laser
betterquesting.quest.nqmqybchRzWn-T46-3vHmQ.desc=§2This quest provides an optional retrieval task for two small lasers capable of running Helium-4 - Hydrogen Fuel at 15MHE.§r%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_ICFLASER.png[/img]

# Quest: UFO
betterquesting.quest.q0Q4S7F-QlCzGWDkdOBMqw.name=UFO
betterquesting.quest.q0Q4S7F-QlCzGWDkdOBMqw.desc=The Martian Invasion Ship is a late-game boss which is killed to get the §6UFO Coin§r, used in crafting Gerald.%n%nThis quest provides an alternative way of obtaining the coin.%n%n§2This quest can be repeated.

# Quest: Welded Osmiridium Plate
betterquesting.quest.xYmNHPDAQkSwXHOow8--4g.name=Welded Osmiridium Plate
betterquesting.quest.xYmNHPDAQkSwXHOow8--4g.desc=§6Welded Osmiridium Plates§r cost 300 Billion §eHE§r to produce, so good energy generation and storage infrastructure is needed.


## Quest Line: NTM: Space
betterquesting.questline.enTskTtvRdajee3UMSgXKg.name=NTM: Space
betterquesting.questline.enTskTtvRdajee3UMSgXKg.desc=Explore Space and colonise planets. This chapter revolves around the content of NTM: Space.

# Quest: Duna
betterquesting.quest.-aAyklEkSHK7wGxEEzQJ9Q.name=Duna
betterquesting.quest.-aAyklEkSHK7wGxEEzQJ9Q.desc=The red planet, home to vast quantities of §6Iron§r. §6Molysite§r and §6Volcano Gems§r can be found here in basaltic caves, found within basins where vast oceans were theorized to once exist.

# Quest: Mobile Orbital Station
betterquesting.quest.0PWQEKZ0QnWgh33WE1jS2A.name=Mobile Orbital Station
betterquesting.quest.0PWQEKZ0QnWgh33WE1jS2A.desc=By having an orbital station have an §3Orbital Station Computer§r and §3Drop Pods§r, one can move their station to any destination they wish, massively cutting down on material costs needed to make new rockets.

# Quest: Dyson Swarms
betterquesting.quest.3WDOW4oRQoO6WN6291ZuNw.name=Dyson Swarms
betterquesting.quest.3WDOW4oRQoO6WN6291ZuNw.desc=§3Dyson Swarms§r consist of thousands of swarm members encircling the parent star of a system, and energy production from the swarm scales based on the number of members in a swarm. These satellites do not last indefinitely however, they attenuate (decay) over time, with the chance of decay increasing as the number of swarm members increase.%n%n§6Dyson Swarm Members§r must be launched into solar orbit via the use of a huge centrifugal launch platform, known as the §3Spinlauncher§r. The spinlauncher launches 4 swarm members at a time, consuming a large amount of electricity to do so.%n%nThe §3Dyson Receiver§r is the main machine required for collecting energy from the swarm. It collimates the immense energy collected from the swarm into a immensely powerful beam. Setting up requires only a satellite ID chip that is matched to an existing swarm. The energy beam must be pointed towards a Dyson Power Converter.%n%nThe §3Satellite Dyson Relay§r can be used to allow dyson swarms to provide power during night time.

# Quest: CMB Insert
betterquesting.quest.3fvMK3HASiaG4E0wg7MTrA.name=CMB Insert
betterquesting.quest.3fvMK3HASiaG4E0wg7MTrA.desc=§6CMB Iserts§r are an armor modification which will protect its user from the corrosive atmosphere of §eEve§r. %n%nThe §3Gas Giant Harvester§r will return back with §bJool Air§r, to be processed by the §3Cryogenic Distillation Machine§r.

# Quest: Industrial Greenhouse
betterquesting.quest.4HLGI5HyQtSw1G-iuwI0kg.name=Industrial Greenhouse
betterquesting.quest.4HLGI5HyQtSw1G-iuwI0kg.desc=The §3Industrial Greenhouse§r converts §bCarbon Dioxide§r into §bOxygen§r via crop growth. The greenhouse can also be supplied with §6Fertilizer§r for faster growing.

# Quest: Drop Pod
betterquesting.quest.6YickkEnS--aDKBPtI6nrg.name=Drop Pod
betterquesting.quest.6YickkEnS--aDKBPtI6nrg.desc=With a §3Drop pod§r, one can access their space station without needing to build new rockets. They can also be used to land on other planets once the station has reached them.%n%n§2Make sure to keep spare drives.§r

# Quest: Dyson Anatmogenesis Terraformer
betterquesting.quest.6k-JrbD-S8GO9PRRthWNRA.name=Dyson Anatmogenesis Terraformer
betterquesting.quest.6k-JrbD-S8GO9PRRthWNRA.desc=The §3Dyson Anatmogenesis Terraformer§r provides the most utility out of all the currently available §3Dyson converters§r, accepting a beam from a receiver and providing a direct energy to mass conversion, producing planetary scale atmospheric gases, terraforming any planet or moon as a player sees fit.%n%nBy default it will release oxygen into an atmosphere, making it breathable once it crosses the 0.1atm threshold for breathing. A fluid identifier can be used to switch the gas emitted, and a screwdriver can switch it between emitting or extracting gases from the atmosphere.%n%nIf powered with §e150THE/s§r power from a swarm (equivalent to a swarm size of 1,024), it will take 8 hours to reach 0.1atm of pressure.

# Quest: Cryogenic Distillation Machine
betterquesting.quest.7kkbpR6rS4CsUTUFQ5wd7g.name=Cryogenic Distillation Machine
betterquesting.quest.7kkbpR6rS4CsUTUFQ5wd7g.desc=The §3Cryogenic Distillation Machine§r can split atmospheric gases into 4 useful fractions, like for example, taking trace amounts of §bNitrogen§r out of the Dunaian atmosphere to produce soil for planting crops.

# Quest: Teleporter
betterquesting.quest.8j7JCxPeSaaBqlOTrRGtCg.name=Teleporter
betterquesting.quest.8j7JCxPeSaaBqlOTrRGtCg.desc=The §3Teleporter§r can be used to teleport players, and entities in general, to a specific location.%n%nRight-click a block with the §6Telelinker§r to set the desired exit position, then shift-click the teleporter with the telelinker to configure the teleporter.%n%n§2The teleporter is a one way trip so it is advised that multiple are made.%n%nInterdimensional teleportation using teleporters requires a very expensive type of fuel, so it is recommended that other teleportations methods are used, such as AE2 Spatial.

# Quest: Steam Radiator
betterquesting.quest.AB-0K2UoQF-7uQ9XiO8mqw.name=Steam Radiator
betterquesting.quest.AB-0K2UoQF-7uQ9XiO8mqw.desc=The §3Steam Radiator§r is a steam condenser that works in the vacuum of space.

# Quest: Gallium Arsenide
betterquesting.quest.DeOqQyXwQRq5RNcDa5l0ug.name=Gallium Arsenide
betterquesting.quest.DeOqQyXwQRq5RNcDa5l0ug.desc=§6Gallium Arsenide§r is made from mixing §6Gallium§r, which can be procured by processing rich mineral deposits from §eMoho§r or §eIke§r, and §6Arsenic§r which is found on Ike in bedrock ore, or on §eEarth§r via dirt and stone that has been damaged by hydraulic fracking.

# Quest: Vacuum Solderer
betterquesting.quest.G3Em4SXiQee1Yu-Rd0yGaA.name=Vacuum Solderer
betterquesting.quest.G3Em4SXiQee1Yu-Rd0yGaA.desc=The §3Vacuum Solderer§r is a machine that can only function in a vacuum, and produces vacuum circuits. They can be placed into the §3Drive Processor§r to enable it to process higher tier planetary drives.

# Quest: Space Equipment
betterquesting.quest.HvPzivF4SWWIDt5syO87xA.name=Space Equipment
betterquesting.quest.HvPzivF4SWWIDt5syO87xA.desc=The §6PLSS§r is an armor modification which will allow you to breathe in space. It will only work on airtight sealed suits.%n%nThe §6Heavy Boots§r can be used to quickly descend down in low-gravity environments.

# Quest: Magma Drill
betterquesting.quest.IaIkbc7YQeuiRONmPZSqdw.name=Magma Drill
betterquesting.quest.IaIkbc7YQeuiRONmPZSqdw.desc=The §3Magma Drill§r is a Moho exclusive machine which extracts §bMineral-Rich Magma§r to be processed into §6Gallium§r and §6Arsenic§r. Simply centrifuge the §6Vulcanite§r to obtain the resourses.%n%n§2Slag and Mineral-Rich Magma Share one port.§r

# Quest: Ike
betterquesting.quest.KItM5UOCSNmCMNKnohadaQ.name=Ike
betterquesting.quest.KItM5UOCSNmCMNKnohadaQ.desc=§eIke§r, the sole moon of §eDuna§r, has hints of a past as a significant hazardous waste dump, with large spires and pyramids reminiscent of potential designs on Earth for warning future civilizations of great danger in relation to nuclear waste. §eMeteor dungeons§r spawn more frequently here, and pools of §bAlkyl Bromide§r can be found on the surface.%n

# Quest: Drive Processor Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.LKTbDe35Rte7XOisZoywOQ.name=Drive Processor Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.LKTbDe35Rte7XOisZoywOQ.desc=The §3Drive Processor Tier 3§r allows for travel to §eLaythe§r.

# Quest: Hydrazine
betterquesting.quest.M5NifoAtR2mnDAQpi9qfHg.name=Hydrazine
betterquesting.quest.M5NifoAtR2mnDAQpi9qfHg.desc=§bHydrazine§r is a powerful rocket fuel which is needed to operate a §3Drop Pod§r.

# Quest: Atmospheric Scanner
betterquesting.quest.MqqnLpS-RLK6oNw12wzI7Q.name=Atmospheric Scanner
betterquesting.quest.MqqnLpS-RLK6oNw12wzI7Q.desc=The §6Atmospheric Scanner§r shows the atmospheric consistency of planets. Useful for when terraforming.

# Quest: Orbital Station
betterquesting.quest.NBDAp_kvThGG5C4yE0SiPA.name=Orbital Station
betterquesting.quest.NBDAp_kvThGG5C4yE0SiPA.desc=The §3Orbital Station§r is a space station which is located at the orbit of §eEarth§r. §3Solar Panels§r in combination with §3Air Vents§r can be used to make a sustainable living environment in the station. Make sure to make airlocks to minimise air loss.

# Quest: Stainless Steel
betterquesting.quest.Q0hC3CjIR4GB7MtYPpxXgA.name=Stainless Steel
betterquesting.quest.Q0hC3CjIR4GB7MtYPpxXgA.desc=§6Stainless Steel§r is an alloy made of §6Steel§r and §6Nickel§r.

# Quest: Drive Processor Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.QVJAi3JOR5in6VwMOEyL6w.name=Drive Processor Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.QVJAi3JOR5in6VwMOEyL6w.desc=The §3Drive Processor Tier 2§r allows for travel to §eDres§r and §eEve§r.

# Quest: Hafnium
betterquesting.quest.S0AQWdCYSeiUnhi2CmLszA.name=Hafnium
betterquesting.quest.S0AQWdCYSeiUnhi2CmLszA.desc=§6Hafnium§r is a rare light metal needed to produce the §6Hafnium chips§r, which at this stage in progression can only be obtained by centrifuging niobium crystals, which must be created from niobium ore, only found on §eDres§r and §eEve§r.

# Quest: Mun/Minmus
betterquesting.quest.SyNchvx5TpG6S7lF4jtiOA.name=Mun/Minmus
betterquesting.quest.SyNchvx5TpG6S7lF4jtiOA.desc=Your first destination! Absolutely chock full of §6Lithium§r, §6Quartz§r and most importantly your first source of §6Nickel§r to start producing §6Stainless Steel§r for space-grade machinery. The §eMun§r is the first atmosphere-less body available in a regular playthrough, necessary for making the first tier of §6Drive Processors§r in the §3Vacuum Solderer§r.%n%nThe B-Side destination alternative to the Mun, §eMinmus§r is characterized by a distinctive mint-choc-chip ice-cream aesthetic. §3Pumps§r function here, but instead of producing §bWater§r, this moon bizarrely produces §bMilk§r, allowing for full automation of §6Butter§r, §6Milkshakes§r and §6Ice-Cream§r.

# Quest: Laythe
betterquesting.quest.Tz9bzhSZQLGbAIEh4Zckbg.name=Laythe
betterquesting.quest.Tz9bzhSZQLGbAIEh4Zckbg.desc=A beautiful water world, teeming with life, oceans lit up with fields of glowgrass. §bJool gas§r can be harvested from here using a §3Gas Giant Harvester§r.

# Quest: Drive Processor Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.VetSLWDYS8OTb7T4X9aAEw.name=Drive Processor Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.VetSLWDYS8OTb7T4X9aAEw.desc=§3Drive Processor Tier 1§r allows for travel to §eDuna§r, §eDres§r and §eMoho§r.

# Quest: Brine Processing
betterquesting.quest.WRZqHx4ZRia4S1zEWYFg-Q.name=Brine Processing
betterquesting.quest.WRZqHx4ZRia4S1zEWYFg-Q.desc=§bBrine§r, which is found in deposits similar to oil ones on earth, can be processed to obtain materials such as §6Nickel§r, §6Copper§r and §6Sulfur§r, and fluids such as §bHydrogen§r and §bOxygen§r.

# Quest: Rocket Preparations
betterquesting.quest.XFyuo3SLQbmHtU7FcYdZ1g.name=Rocket Preparations
betterquesting.quest.XFyuo3SLQbmHtU7FcYdZ1g.desc=Due to the expansive nature of rocket assembly, it is highly recommend that the wiki is checked out as it provides more information.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Vehicle_Assembly_Base_(NTM:_Space)[/url]

# Quest: Stardar and Drive Processor
betterquesting.quest.ZPfHiJvPQIutgvhSROlbeQ.name=Stardar and Drive Processor
betterquesting.quest.ZPfHiJvPQIutgvhSROlbeQ.desc=The §3StarDar§r is your base of operations for mission planning, helping you to locate and scan potential landing zones on planets, and §6Program Drives§r that can be inserted into your rocket's astronavigational systems to make journeys to said planets.%n%nThe §3Drive Processor§r processes drives that have been programmed by the StarDar, allowing them to be inserted into rocket navigation computers.

# Quest: Atmospheric Compressor
betterquesting.quest.aZBaZGfVRHeXWmLqDHjuUw.name=Atmospheric Compressor
betterquesting.quest.aZBaZGfVRHeXWmLqDHjuUw.desc=The §3Atmospheric Compressor§r collects air from different planets. In combination with a §3Cryogenic Distillation Machine§r it can produce many useful fluids and gasses.

# Quest: Alkylation Unit
betterquesting.quest.icj9Y8q0QiWjFk2g7dTnww.name=Alkylation Unit
betterquesting.quest.icj9Y8q0QiWjFk2g7dTnww.desc=The §3Alkylation Unit§r is designed to convert lighter hydrocarbons into useful heavier hydrocarbon products. From §bNatural Gas§r it can produce §bUnsaturated§r and §bAromatic hydrocarbons§r, commonly used for §6Rubber§r and §6Bakelite§r, and even produce §bBTX§r via the use of §bHigh-Performance Solvent§r. As a utility, it can also alkylate §bPetroleum Gas§r into §bLight Oil§r.

# Quest: Air Vent
betterquesting.quest.jiPDr_h5RrqHUkzMYkuhpQ.name=Air Vent
betterquesting.quest.jiPDr_h5RrqHUkzMYkuhpQ.desc=The §3Air Vent§r is used to supply a sealed room with §3§r§bOxygen§r to make it breathable. Make sure to construct an airlock (2 doors with space between them) before entering or exiting the space base or else the air will be sucked out.

# Quest: CO2 Scrubber
betterquesting.quest.mtikmzS9T1SXk8ysQvCckA.name=CO2 Scrubber
betterquesting.quest.mtikmzS9T1SXk8ysQvCckA.desc=The §3CO2 Scrubber§r allows you to recover §bCarbon Dioxide§r from a pressurized room. This is useful when building space stations with §3Industrial Greenhouses§r.

# Quest: Microgravity Algae Film
betterquesting.quest.nfgxBE2jRE2InE-vMVEfRQ.name=Microgravity Algae Film
betterquesting.quest.nfgxBE2jRE2InE-vMVEfRQ.desc=The §3Microgravity Algae Film§r is a machine is made of specialized layers of laythe plants that will convert §bCarbon Dioxide§r directly into §bLiquid Oxygen§r. They however only function when in orbit.

# Quest: Dairy Processing Tank
betterquesting.quest.pEUat2aAT9az1GdhM3wvUA.name=Dairy Processing Tank
betterquesting.quest.pEUat2aAT9az1GdhM3wvUA.desc=The §3Dairy Processing Tank§r, while it can be crafted earlier, is very useful on Minmus because of the infinite §bMilk§r production from §3Pumps§r. It can be used to process milk into different liquids, which can then be used to make food items.

# Quest: Dres
betterquesting.quest.rkMKa7TCT5u0jJsdH6TWnw.name=Dres
betterquesting.quest.rkMKa7TCT5u0jJsdH6TWnw.desc=This planet has some of the most prized resources in the whole system, with even the primary fraction of bedrock ore consisting of incredibly valuable metals and materials. §6Niobium§r, §6Coltan§r, and §6Lanthanium§r ore is present here in vast quantities.

# Quest: Orbital Station Computer
betterquesting.quest.sh6JGXJTRq2RSJp3UcQEeQ.name=Orbital Station Computer
betterquesting.quest.sh6JGXJTRq2RSJp3UcQEeQ.desc=The §3Orbital Station Computer§r, when having a drive inserted into it, can move the station to its destination.%n%n§3Thrusters§r with fuel are required to be attached to the station.

# Quest: Tekto
betterquesting.quest.tryLG0jySbGKMHzTFhvWOA.name=Tekto
betterquesting.quest.tryLG0jySbGKMHzTFhvWOA.desc=A strange world, similar to §eEarth§r, where life is different because the vegetation, the only form of life there, is made of complex polymers, like rubber§r and plastic§r.%n%nTekto bedrock ore doesn’t have the non-metal variant; instead, it is replaced by the plastic variant, from which the player can obtain §6Polymer§r, §6Rubber§r, §6Semtex§r and §6PVC§r.

# Quest: Rocket Transporter Pad
betterquesting.quest.utoxNiUARPOk7qRfnpN0Og.name=Rocket Transporter Pad
betterquesting.quest.utoxNiUARPOk7qRfnpN0Og.desc=The §3Rocket Transporter Pads§r can be used to transport items and fluids between celestial bodies, making them essential for setting up bedrock ore processing plants.%n%n§2Rocket Transporter Pads can be used to send spatial cells between celestial bodies, allowing for cheap teleportation.

# Quest: Eve
betterquesting.quest.vWpv_FM5QYqYHsRsaNNwog.name=Eve
betterquesting.quest.vWpv_FM5QYqYHsRsaNNwog.desc=While it is possible to travel here with only a tier 2 drive processor to exploit the incredibly powerful schrabidic resources that exist here, players will not last long without the appropriate armor inserts, due to the highly corrosive atmosphere melting any armor it comes into contact with.%n

# Quest: Rocket Assembling and Launching
betterquesting.quest.w4uLB-JtTW-fCQA_qF6_ww.name=Rocket Assembling and Launching
betterquesting.quest.w4uLB-JtTW-fCQA_qF6_ww.desc=The §3Vehicle Assembly Base§r is a structure which is one of the most vital parts of your space-faring efforts. It'll allow you to stack your rockets and plan out each segment of your journey. Note that each rocket stage allows for one launch from a celestial body to another, so a two-stage rocket can make a round-trip between, say, the Earth and the Mun.%n%nThe §3Rocket Launch Pad§r is the only launch pad capable of supporting the various fuel loads and complex requirements of the stacked rockets. This is the only way to fuel up a rocket too, so you'll want to make multiple stages for launching from bodies without a pad. The pad itself has a GUI that'll indicate what your rocket requires to be launched.

# Quest: Solar Panel
betterquesting.quest.xY1aWGAjTUGOWEhAdJ9kRw.name=Solar Panel
betterquesting.quest.xY1aWGAjTUGOWEhAdJ9kRw.desc=§3Solar Panels§r are a cheap way of producing power in space, producing §e2kHe/s§r.

# Quest: Moho
betterquesting.quest.yWu2LtytQjGg65tFXTo2ow.name=Moho
betterquesting.quest.yWu2LtytQjGg65tFXTo2ow.desc=A fair-dinkum planet, hot as hell, and full of rare resources generally only found in the Nether. §6Australium§r is only found here, in vast quantities deep under the surface. Some of the largest caves ever generated within Minecraft can be found here.


## Quest Line: Bedrock Ore Processing
betterquesting.questline.idsx5LoxT9WXsZ2oWoP4wg.name=Bedrock Ore Processing
betterquesting.questline.idsx5LoxT9WXsZ2oWoP4wg.desc=Learn how to process Bedrock Ores for infinite resourses.

# Quest: Roasted Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.073YOAqUQpGxoX5HnU5VqA.name=Roasted Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.073YOAqUQpGxoX5HnU5VqA.desc=Most ore processing stages can be passed through a §3Combination Oven§r or a §3Pyrolysis Oven§r to produce §bVitriol§r. The ore itself will not be affected by this process - yielding the same outputs whether or not the ore is roasted - so this can be done to add bonus byproducts (from processing the vitriol) effectively for free.

# Quest: Roasted Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.0jPPiKf3TsmtGbv9-y-FMQ.name=Roasted Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.0jPPiKf3TsmtGbv9-y-FMQ.desc=Product of third roasting.

# Quest: Ore Slop
betterquesting.quest.3cxFoKHGSHmwhLh4rTMHVg.name=Ore Slop
betterquesting.quest.3cxFoKHGSHmwhLh4rTMHVg.desc=§bOre Slop§r§r can be processed most efficiently in an §3Electrolysis Machine§r, giving §6Mercury§r, §6Niter§r, §6Sulfur§r and §6Limestone§r. Products obtained from the processing can be used to make acids for the rest of the bedrock ore plant.

# Quest: Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.6pZz1HhdRIuMhK-Jey8oTA.name=Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.6pZz1HhdRIuMhK-Jey8oTA.desc=Product of Second Centrifuging.

# Quest: Roasted Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.7VfzcDkmQU2egBpwxRs4Fg.name=Roasted Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.7VfzcDkmQU2egBpwxRs4Fg.desc=Product of third roasting.

# Quest: Washed Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.7ymDZyp4SqiscLJOSI2zGw.name=Washed Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.7ymDZyp4SqiscLJOSI2zGw.desc=Product of second water washing.

# Quest: Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.8iNCagWWTD-29ECY764xsA.name=Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.8iNCagWWTD-29ECY764xsA.desc=Product of second centrifuging.

# Quest: Bedrock Ore Crumbs
betterquesting.quest.9UCrVSLuT663wp3s6K2AiQ.name=Bedrock Ore Crumbs
betterquesting.quest.9UCrVSLuT663wp3s6K2AiQ.desc=Some steps will produce crumbs which can be further processed into more primary outputs in an arc furnace or electrolyzer, or combined into a full stack of 64 and washed with §bOre Slop§r to produce more unprocessed ore, which can be passed back into the system to yield even more ores.

# Quest: Roasted Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.BcWOg0FzQZSP3Z4OscWEUA.name=Roasted Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.BcWOg0FzQZSP3Z4OscWEUA.desc=Product of third roasting.

# Quest: Washed Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.CNzJA-nTSEi9nNMW9Pq9Fg.name=Washed Sulfuric Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.CNzJA-nTSEi9nNMW9Pq9Fg.desc=Product of second water washing.

# Quest: Sulfuric Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.DU8UbUuGR0moBP6vGSiH6w.name=Sulfuric Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.DU8UbUuGR0moBP6vGSiH6w.desc=There are multiple ways of processing at this stage, most efficient being the §3Arc Furnace§r.

# Quest: Primary Fraction, Adjustable Wheights
betterquesting.quest.E0QxGJQuRoiEUP7GO7PYdw.name=Primary Fraction, Adjustable Wheights
betterquesting.quest.E0QxGJQuRoiEUP7GO7PYdw.desc=Increase primary or secondary products with §bHydrogen§r or §bChlorine Gas§r.

# Quest: Cleaned Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.QjmRsA1iSc2nvV0Fq5TVBg.name=Cleaned Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.QjmRsA1iSc2nvV0Fq5TVBg.desc=There are multiple ways of processing at this stage, most efficient being the §3Arc Furnace§r.

# Quest: Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.XM83SUU1QpSooqGDwIm5vw.name=Dissolved Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.XM83SUU1QpSooqGDwIm5vw.desc=Product of second centrifuging.

# Quest: Centrifuged Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.gfxplb02SayHVcvrjg5wQw.name=Centrifuged Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.gfxplb02SayHVcvrjg5wQw.desc=All ores must be processed in a §3Centrifuge§r in order to extract products from them. The first stage of centrifuging will produce a second stage of ore which can either be centrifuged again to immediately get primary products and finish processing, or can be washed with solvents to acquire useful byproducts.%n%nGravel obtained from centrifuging can be processed into concrete for base building, in a §3SILEX§r for additional byproducts, such as §6Lithium§r and §6Boron§r, or shredded into sand for §6Silicon§r.

# Quest: Second Bedrock Ore Roasting
betterquesting.quest.hvETQYjrT6iyC1DN019FRw.name=Second Bedrock Ore Roasting
betterquesting.quest.hvETQYjrT6iyC1DN019FRw.desc=Roast your bedrock ore again for additional §bVitriol§r.

# Quest: Solvent Washed Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.iaXjcyplQc-ijtFP1Mvvfw.name=Solvent Washed Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.iaXjcyplQc-ijtFP1Mvvfw.desc=After the first centrifuging stage, ores can be washed with various fluids to increase primary products or add byproducts, these include:%n%n§s§bSulfuric Acid§r - adds the first tier of byproducts to your outputs%n%n§bSolvent§r - adds the second tier of byproducts%n%n§bHigh-Performance Solvent§r - adds the final tier of byproducts%n%n§bLiquid Hydrogen§r - increases the yield of the first primary product%n%n§bChlorine Gas§r - increases the yield of the second primary product%n%n§2Note that processing with higher tier solvents will produce lower tier products as well, meaning processing with HPS will provide all available byproducts. Ores processed with lower tier solvents can be processed again with higher tiers to further increase yields, doubling outputs each time!

# Quest: Vitriol
betterquesting.quest.lLZ1OeE6TlOFsiKNKu5p3Q.name=Vitriol
betterquesting.quest.lLZ1OeE6TlOFsiKNKu5p3Q.desc=§bVitriol§r is the best way to obtain §bChlorine Gas§r from processing it in an §3Electrolysis Machine§r, with additional byproducts of §bSulfuric Acid§r and §bIron§r.

# Quest: Dissolved Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.lf0M379oRhK6Wtt1u1yzJg.name=Dissolved Byproducts Products
betterquesting.quest.lf0M379oRhK6Wtt1u1yzJg.desc=There are multiple ways of processing at this stage, most efficient being the §3Arc Furnace§r.

# Quest: Seperated Clean Primary Fraction
betterquesting.quest.rry4J7v5QNKgPYI9lxubRA.name=Seperated Clean Primary Fraction
betterquesting.quest.rry4J7v5QNKgPYI9lxubRA.desc=Product of Second Centrifuging.

# Quest: Second Bedrock Ore Centrifuging
betterquesting.quest.spY0QgAGTZmd3mNacRqDjQ.name=Second Bedrock Ore Centrifuging
betterquesting.quest.spY0QgAGTZmd3mNacRqDjQ.desc=Centrifuge your Solvent Washed Bedrock ores to seperate primary and secondary products.%n%n§2The following quests will assume that High-Performance Solvent is used.

# Quest: Washed Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.wNqkx13BS-SWoF9mDFzYsg.name=Washed Cleaned Byproduct
betterquesting.quest.wNqkx13BS-SWoF9mDFzYsg.desc=Product of second water washing.

# Quest: Primary Fraction Products
betterquesting.quest.xbBcX3xpTDau2oGgLWMulA.name=Primary Fraction Products
betterquesting.quest.xbBcX3xpTDau2oGgLWMulA.desc=There are multiple ways of processing at this stage, most efficient being the §3Electrolysis Machine§r.

# Quest: Raw Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.yuW7Zn_hSPiU8WZmFSY6lQ.name=Raw Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.yuW7Zn_hSPiU8WZmFSY6lQ.desc=The first step to processing §eRaw Bedrock Ore§r straight out of the ground is to run it through a §3Bedrock Ore Processor§r. This will split the raw ore into general types, with amounts depending on the location the ore was extracted and any effectiveness upgrades. These types are:%n%n§eLight Metal§r - common metals including §6Iron/Copper§r%n%n§eHeavy Metal§r - heavier metals including §6Tungsten/Lead§r%n%n§eRare Earth§r - rare earth metals including §6Cobalt/Rare Earth§r%n%n§eActinide§r - radioactive heavy metals including §6Uranium/Thorium§r%n%n§eNon-Metal§r - non-metallic ores including §6Coal/Sulfur§r%n%n§eCrystalline§r - crystals including §6Redstone/Cinnabar§r

# Quest: Water Washed Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.z95ToI2RQdSvpi_xIa2Tew.name=Water Washed Bedrock Ore
betterquesting.quest.z95ToI2RQdSvpi_xIa2Tew.desc=Ores can be washed to increase the number of primary products and even add useful additional byproducts. Washing is done in §3Ore Acidizers§r with different fluids.%n%nOres straight out of the §3Bedrock Ore Processor§r (before initial centrifuging) can be washed with §bWater§r to immediately duplicate all products, making it a very desirable first step.


## Quest Line: Particle Physics
betterquesting.questline.SB7ygaq5RhWTSHk13qSDGA.name=Particle Physics
betterquesting.questline.SB7ygaq5RhWTSHk13qSDGA.desc=Collide Particles together to create new materials.

# Quest: Exposure Chamber
betterquesting.quest.1dJ5iJNbQ26XKKVjlR0Wsg.name=Exposure Chamber
betterquesting.quest.1dJ5iJNbQ26XKKVjlR0Wsg.desc=The §3Exposure Chamber§r is a machine in which many materials can be created by exposing ingots to certain particles, most important of which being §6Dineutronium§r.

# Quest: Muon
betterquesting.quest.4dUQV5uHRiuVbPZQK-Tb-A.name=Muon
betterquesting.quest.4dUQV5uHRiuVbPZQK-Tb-A.desc=§6Muon Particles§r are created by colliding §bAntimatter§r and §bHydrogen§r. A second loop with §6NbTi Coils§r are required.

# Quest: Strange Quark
betterquesting.quest.6gWNwAbqSwauVebymWHlKA.name=Strange Quark
betterquesting.quest.6gWNwAbqSwauVebymWHlKA.desc=§6Strange Quark§r is made from colliding §6Muon§r and §6Dark Matter§r particles.

# Quest: Dark Matter
betterquesting.quest.8gdmudEZRRWDbmt_SgkifQ.name=Dark Matter
betterquesting.quest.8gdmudEZRRWDbmt_SgkifQ.desc=§6Dark Matter§r is made from colliding two §bAntischrabidium§r particles together. A third loop with §6BSCCO Coils§r is required.

# Quest: Chicken Nugget
betterquesting.quest.DJQ2vE3LQ0e5pmnrwbNNkA.name=Chicken Nugget
betterquesting.quest.DJQ2vE3LQ0e5pmnrwbNNkA.desc=The §6Chicken Nugget§r is the best food item in the mod, completely filling up both hunger and saturation. It is made by colliding 2 raw chickens in a Particle Accelerator.

# Quest: Particle Accelerator Components
betterquesting.quest.OCvBq3i-Q5CCZdpP4UKNKQ.name=Particle Accelerator Components
betterquesting.quest.OCvBq3i-Q5CCZdpP4UKNKQ.desc=The §3Particle Accelerator§r is highly modular and as such has many parts, each serving a different function:%n%n§3Particle Source§r: To create the particle.%n%n§3Particle Detector§r (at a receiving end): To form the intended byproduct.%n%n§3Quadrupole Magnets§r: To reduce particle defocus.%n%n§3RF Cavities§r: For electromagnetic acceleration.%n%n§3Dipole Magnets§r: For re-directing the particle.%n%n§6Coils§r: For quadrupole and dipole magnets to function.

# Quest: Murky Anvil
betterquesting.quest.UaqsY4yyStKS223fr9qVQg.name=Murky Anvil
betterquesting.quest.UaqsY4yyStKS223fr9qVQg.desc=The§3 Murky Anvil§r is the ultimate version of the §3Anvil§r, having all recipes unlocked.

# Quest: The Digamma Particle
betterquesting.quest.Vq7_230-TPKFYERt7zynAg.name=The Digamma Particle
betterquesting.quest.Vq7_230-TPKFYERt7zynAg.desc=The §c§r§4§r§6Digamma Particle§r is created by colliding a §6Sparkticle Capsule§r with a §6Higgs Boson Capsule§r in a §3Particle Accelerator§r. Making it in the particle accelerator will require §6Chlorophyte Coils§r and a fourth loop, at a momentum of 70,000.%n%nThe digamma particle emits a different kind of radiation, §4DRX§r, which currently can only be countered by the use of digamma medication, most notably §6Enteramine Pills§r, which provide full immunity against DRX for 10 minutes. After the §3DFC§r, Fau armor can be crafted which provides full resistance against DRX.

# Quest: Additional Particle Accelerator Information
betterquesting.quest.WONE5CQBTMCVbCuGUZqXpQ.name=Additional Particle Accelerator Information
betterquesting.quest.WONE5CQBTMCVbCuGUZqXpQ.desc=Particle Accelerators§r are either two types; linear (straight) or circular (synchronous) accelerators. Since circles do not exist in Minecraft, synchronous accelerators are square in design. They are both modular and can be built to any size, with the only restriction being resources, intended byproduct, and energy costs.%n%nMost of the components within particle accelerators require cooling via §bCold Perfluoromethyl§r. The hot perfluoromethyl can be redirected to a §3Compressor§r for re-cooling, creating a feedback loop despite energy loss.%n%nParticles start slowly and accelerate. Particles only do 1 component per tick, which increases by 1 every 1,000 momentum%n%nUsing a §6Screwdriver§r on a beamline toggles a window which flashes if a particle passes.%n%nThe particle accelerator requires couple §eMHEs§r to function properly. Fission reactors or fusion can be used to meet these power needs.

# Quest: Higgs Boson
betterquesting.quest._1073ZttSUe0lJA38cUXeg.name=Higgs Boson
betterquesting.quest._1073ZttSUe0lJA38cUXeg.desc=§6Higgs Boson§r particles are created by colliding §6Lead Ions§r with §bHydrogen§r. A second loop with §6NbTi Coils§r are required. Can be also used to easily transmutate §6Uranium§r into §6Schrabidium§r in an §3Exposure Chamber§r.

# Quest: Tachyon
betterquesting.quest.aVHAKgP-QQ-5HsJuMR5png.name=Tachyon
betterquesting.quest.aVHAKgP-QQ-5HsJuMR5png.desc=§6Tachyon§r particles are created by colliding §6Higgs Boson§r and §6Muon particles§r.

# Quest: Digamma Laser Crystal
betterquesting.quest.cDlOz30sQj6CDezzCvteDw.name=Digamma Laser Crystal
betterquesting.quest.cDlOz30sQj6CDezzCvteDw.desc=The §6Digamma Laser Crystal§r is the fastest and final laser crystal which can be used in a SILEX.%n%n§2If the laser touches any block, the surrounding area will be atomized.

# Quest: Dineutronium
betterquesting.quest.gU8OT9pvSsaHXXvZZUn6sw.name=Dineutronium
betterquesting.quest.gU8OT9pvSsaHXXvZZUn6sw.desc=§6Dineutronium§r is the mod's (almost) ultimate material. It's a final tier material and is a higher tier than even §6Euphemium§r. It is very difficult to produce and it's used to make the most absurd and broken items this mod has. The only material that is more difficult to make, would be §6Osmiridium§r.

# Quest: Particle Accelerator Looping
betterquesting.quest.hnI3TTSoSDytvFuil-40pg.name=Particle Accelerator Looping
betterquesting.quest.hnI3TTSoSDytvFuil-40pg.desc=§2For recipes that demand high momentum, additional loops are needed. This quest serves as a guide on how to change the direction of particles.§r%n%nBelow is a miniature particle accelerator built for showcasing purposes. It is not connected to power, coolant or have any coils. It does not have rf cavities and uses two particle detectors as outputs. A compass is also provided in the image.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA1.png[/img]%n%nAfter constructing your PA, assuming the beamlines face the right directions, head over to the magnet that bridges the first and second loops.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA2.png[/img]%n%nOpen its GUI and configure the dipole magnet. %n%nThe first line is for particles that havent reached the desired momentum. %n%nThe second line is for particles that have reached the desired momentum. %n%nThe third line is for particles that have reached the desired momentum AND are powered by redstone.%n%nThe §cRed Line§r shows the direction the particle will travel towards and the §9Blue Line§r shows where the player is facing.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA3.png[/img]%n%nMake sure that for this specific dipole magnet the third line has the particle orientation facing towards the second loop, NORTH in this case.%n%nAfter this, the redstone logic must be set in order to be able to turn the particle orientation when powered. Simply provide power underneath the dipole magnet as such. A redstone signal should only exist when a particle needs momentum greater than what the first tier of coil allows.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA4.png[/img]%n%nHead over, WEST in this case, to the dipole magnet which is after the transitionary dipole and right before the detector, and which connects to the rest of the loop.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA5.png[/img]%n%nOpen its GUI and configure it. Make sure the second line is facing towards the particle detector and the first line towards the other dipole magnets.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_PA6.png[/img]%n%n

# Quest: Murky Wings
betterquesting.quest.kKe1Ghz7R9W-kTBrBA8LLw.name=Murky Wings
betterquesting.quest.kKe1Ghz7R9W-kTBrBA8LLw.desc=§6Murky Wings§r are an armor modification which grants creative flight at super fast speeds.

# Quest: Antischrabidium
betterquesting.quest.q1BhemoLR6maeOr2F5qemw.name=Antischrabidium
betterquesting.quest.q1BhemoLR6maeOr2F5qemw.desc=§bAntischrabidium§r is the gaseous antimatter equivalent of §6Schrabidium§r, typically held in cells and capsules. Much like antimatter, large quantities of antischrabidium must be stored in magnetic antimatter containment barrels.

# Quest: Euphemium
betterquesting.quest.qeqHCCNDQYe89OHgI7zSNQ.name=Euphemium
betterquesting.quest.qeqHCCNDQYe89OHgI7zSNQ.desc=§6Euphemium§r is a fictional material which serves as one of the mod's most endgame materials. It's extremely expensive to produce in large amounts and you will need great advancement through the mod to use it effectively.

# Quest: Sparkticle
betterquesting.quest.zxEqSrCnTC-Ew950yepP3A.name=Sparkticle
betterquesting.quest.zxEqSrCnTC-Ew950yepP3A.desc=§6Sparkticle§r is made from colliding §6Strange Quark§r particles and §6Pulverized Enchantment§r.


## Quest Line: AE2
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABQ.name=AE2
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABQ.desc=Automate your factory using Applied Energistics 2.

# Quest: P2P ME Networking
betterquesting.quest.1bFqt414QEOwMpAVRSd3zg.name=P2P ME Networking
betterquesting.quest.1bFqt414QEOwMpAVRSd3zg.desc=§3P2P ME§r can be used to transport massive amounts of channels without laying many cables.%n%n§2This quest serves as a guide on how to effectively use P2P ME.§r%n%nOnce an §3Energy Acceptor§r has been set up, it is highly recommended (and likely needed) that an §3Energy Cell§r is placed next to it as to ensure that there is enough power going to the system, as more components increase the energy demands of the ME system.%n%nAfter that, 2 §3ME Controllers§r are required, one to provide the channels that machines will use, and another to transport the other's channels by the P2P connections. The top controller can be made bigger by attaching more controllers next to it.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Controller1.png[/img]%n%nAfter the controllers are placed, on the top controller, a P2P Tunnel - ME needs to be placed on any side. The §9Blue Cable§r will serve as the cable that connects the P2P connections, and as such, it needs to be connected to the bottom controller.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Controller2.png[/img]%n%nBy linking the P2P connections together using a §6Memory Card§r, the 32 channels from one side of the top controller will only use 1 channel from the bottom controller to be transported to any destination. The §cRed Cable§r now has access to 32 channels.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Controller3.png[/img]%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Controller4.png[/img]%n%nBy expanding on the previous example, more connections can be added to fully utilize all channels.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Controller5.png[/img]%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_controller6.png[/img]%n

# Quest: P2P Interface Parallelisation
betterquesting.quest.1rIaClFKQbGXrdGi5-Eppg.name=P2P Interface Parallelisation
betterquesting.quest.1rIaClFKQbGXrdGi5-Eppg.desc=Parallelisation of processes can significantly cut down on waiting time and as such it is highly recommended that P2P Interfaces are used.%n%n§2This quest serves as a guide on how to use P2P Interfaces.§r%n%nAs any P2P Connection goes, there needs to be one input, which in this case, holds the §6ME Patterns§r.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_P2P_Interface1.png[/img]%n%nAfter patterns are inserted in the first P2P interface, place down the rest of the output interfaces you want and link them together using a §6Memory Card§r.%n%nIn the image below, the P2P interface highlighted in green stores the patterns, while the ones in blue, are the output ones which will connect machines to the ME system.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_P2P_Interface2.png[/img]%n%nMake sure to have blocking mode enabled on all output P2P interfaces as to prevent clogging and having multiple recipes trying to be executed at once in the same machine.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_P2P_Interface3.png[/img]%n%nFinally, place your desired machines at the output P2P interfaces and add a way of retrieving the items once the operation is done, in this case import buses.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_P2P_Interface4.png[/img]%n

# Quest: ME IO Port
betterquesting.quest.4DM_-wpzThCM_KaSMIPmNA.name=ME IO Port
betterquesting.quest.4DM_-wpzThCM_KaSMIPmNA.desc=The §3ME IO Port§r can transfer the contents of storage cells into an ME Network and back.

# Quest: Spatial IO
betterquesting.quest.5PE7heWhR4qG8AcOcZ0VWQ.name=Spatial IO
betterquesting.quest.5PE7heWhR4qG8AcOcZ0VWQ.desc=§3Spatial IO§r is a way to cut-and-paste physical volumes of space in your world. It works by swapping the defined volume with an identically-sized volume in the spatial storage dimension, sending whatever's in the pylon array to the spatial storage dimension, and whatever's in the dimension to the pylon array.%n%nSpatial IO requires a specific arrangement of its components in order to function, and define the volume to be cut-and-pasted. All of the components must be on the same network in order to function, and you can have only one spatial IO setup on a network. Thus, a subnetwork is recommended.%n%nThe §3Spatial IO Port§r controls the spatial IO operation. It shows stats on the multiblock setup, and holds the spatial cells%n%nTo perform a spatial IO operation, place a §6Spatial Storage Cell§r in the input slot and give the spatial IO port a redstone pulse. It will then swap the volume in the pylons with the volume in the spatial storage dimension. This means that if you send some set of blocks to the spatial storage dimension, then put another set of blocks in the pylons, put the cell back in the input slot, and trigger the IO port again, the 2nd set of blocks will disappear and the 1st set of blcks will reappear.%n%nAny entity in the defined volume, including you, will be carried along, and if you have no way of getting out, you will be trapped in the spatial storage dimension.%n%n§3Spatial Pylons§r are the main part of a spatial IO setup, and define the volume to be affected. The volume is defined by the bounding box of the outside of the pylons, contracted in by 1 block in all directions.

# Quest: AE2 Changes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARg.name=AE2 Changes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARg.desc=In this modpack, §dApplied Energistics 2§r has been changed to fit in more with §dNTM§r. Many components have been changed to include NTM materials and some machines, like the §3Grinder§r and §3Inscriber§r, have had their functions moved to the §3Shredder§r and §3Press§r. The meteors have also been removed, but §6Skystone§r can still be crafted for building purposes.%n%nThis Chapter of the quests has its information derived from the FTB Wiki. If anything else is missing from the quest book, please visit the wiki.%n%n[url]https://ftbwiki.org/Applied_Energistics_2[/url]%n%n§2NTM fluids dont work with AE2.%n

# Quest: Certus Quartz Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARw.name=Certus Quartz Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARw.desc=§6Certus Quartz§r is an important material in AE2. It is dropped when mining or processing certus quartz ore at the rate of one to four, the yield is affected by a tool's Fortune enchantment. Certus Quartz is often interchangeable with vanilla §6Nether Quartz§r in the recipes for basic tools, such as the §6Quartz Cutting Knife§r. Certus quartz ore can be acidized or centrifuged for an increased yield.%n%n§2Certus quartz can later be made in a Chemical Plant using nether quartz.

# Quest: Crystal Growth Chamber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATA.name=Crystal Growth Chamber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATA.desc=The§3 Crystal Growth Chamber§r is a machine in which crystals can grow at an increased speed, while also being in a block instead of being dropped in the ground.

# Quest: Wireless Terminal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXQ.name=Wireless Terminal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAXQ.desc=The §3Security Terminal§r can be used to specify what players are allowed to interact with in the ME network which can be useful in multiplayer. It can also be used to link a §6Wireless Terminal§r to the ME network. Atleast one §3Wireless Access Point§r is required, and its range can be expanded using §6Wireless Boosters§r.

# Quest: Storage Components
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYQ.name=Storage Components
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYQ.desc=The §6ME Storage Housing§r is the outer shell of a §6Storage Cell§r. There are many tiers of storage cells, all of which require the use of NTM machines to be crafted.

# Quest: Fluix Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbA.name=Fluix Crystal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAbA.desc=§6Fluix Crystals§r are another crystal type which is used in crafting recipes throughout the mod. The crystal comes in two forms, the regular fluix crystal and the §6Pure Fluix Crystal§r.%n%nTo create a fluix crystal, 1§6 Charged Certus Quartz§r, 1 §6Nether Quartz§r, and 1 §6Redstone Dust§r must be dropped into a pool of §bWater§r. They will be consumed and output 2 fluix crystals.%n%n§2Fluix crystals can later be made in a Chemical Plant using charged certus quartz and redstone.

# Quest: Crystal Growth Accelerator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcQ.name=Crystal Growth Accelerator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcQ.desc=The §3Crystal Growth Accelerator§r is a machine that uses energy to accelerate the process of crystal purification. This process transforms crystal seeds into pure versions of their fully developed counterparts.

# Quest: Charger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcw.name=Charger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAcw.desc=The §3Charger§r is a machine which will charge §6Certus Quartz Crystals§r into their charged form at the expense of power.

# Quest: Cable Fluix
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeQ.name=Cable Fluix
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeQ.desc=The §6ME Glass Cable - Fluix§r is a cable used to transmit data and energy between devices in an ME Network. It is capable of transmitting §f§e8 channels§r simultaneously.%n%nThe §6Quartz Fiber§r is used to transfer energy, but not channels.%n%n§6Cable Anchors§r can be used to seperate ME cable connections. They can also be used to make §6Facades§r for the cables.

# Quest: Energy Acceptor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAew.name=Energy Acceptor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAew.desc=The §3Energy Acceptor§r transfers energy into the ME system. In combination with an §3HE to RF Converter§r, the ME system can be powered.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_EnergyAcceptor.png[/img]

# Quest: ME Terminal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfA.name=ME Terminal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfA.desc=The §3ME Terminal§r is used to access all available items in the ME Network, including craftable ones.

# Quest: ME Drive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfQ.name=ME Drive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfQ.desc=The §3ME Drive§r serves as the storage of the ME system, in which §6Storage Cells§r can be put and store items.

# Quest: ME Interface
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfg.name=ME Interface
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfg.desc=The §3ME Interface§r is a block which allows the ME Network to interact with machines and inventories. On their own, they can be used to automatically stock inventories, but can be used with §6ME Patterns§r later on for autocrafting.

# Quest: ME Controller
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAgA.name=ME Controller
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAgA.desc=The ME Controller acts as the routing hub of an ME network. It can support up to 8 devices connected to it.

# Quest: ME Buses
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAgg.name=ME Buses
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAgg.desc=The §3ME Export Bus§r is an ME component which is used to export items from the ME network into a machine or other input inventory. %n%nThe §3ME Import Bus§r is an ME component which is used to import items directly into the ME Network from a machine or other output inventory.%n%n§2It is recommended that Interfaces are used over Export/Import buses for performance reasons.

# Quest: Infinity Booster Card
betterquesting.quest.EPrM6umbSw2e8c3-9XF9Wg.name=Infinity Booster Card
betterquesting.quest.EPrM6umbSw2e8c3-9XF9Wg.desc=The §6Infinity Booster Card§r allows one to access their ME system across any distance and dimension. To apply simply open the §6Wireless Crafting Terminal§r and insert the card in it.

# Quest: P2P
betterquesting.quest.Ig84-U5cRH-rxH76bIGE9A.name=P2P
betterquesting.quest.Ig84-U5cRH-rxH76bIGE9A.desc=§6P2P§r Tunnel or "Point to Point Tunnels" are a versatile configurable system to move items / redstone / power / and fluids from one location to another though an existing ME Network without storage.%n%nTunnels are §e1 input to N outputs§r. This means you can output to as many points as you want, but only input at a single point per tunnel.%n%nNetworks can support any number of tunnels, of any different types, and they all function independently.%n%nME tunnels can be used to carry channels from one location to another, and can carry up to §e32 channels§r, same as a §6ME Dense Cable§r, while only requiring a single channel per point, making tunnels a very powerful tool to expand me networks, especially over a distance. However with the great flex-ability they give you comes a limitation, the channel of a p2p tunnel cannot be carried by another p2p tunnel, meaning that you cannot nest them recursively.%n%nTo configure a P2P tunnel you must first attune the tunnel to carry what you want it to, then you need to configure the outputs to their input. You configure the connections by using the §6Memory Card§r. First Shift+Right Click the input to save it on your memory card, then simply right click the different outputs to store the input onto the outputs. this also sets the type of the output to match the type of the input.%n%n§2An advanced version of the Memory Card can also be made, which interacts with the entire network.

# Quest: Wireless Crafting Terminal
betterquesting.quest.Iyj0bDhVRpCgzmAF4vP30A.name=Wireless Crafting Terminal
betterquesting.quest.Iyj0bDhVRpCgzmAF4vP30A.desc=An upgraded version of the §6Wireless Terminal§r, capable of crafting items on the go.%n%n§2The wireless crafting terminal can be added to a bauble slot and used without it being in the inventory. Make sure to set the keybind in the controls menu.§r

# Quest: Interface P2P
betterquesting.quest.Kcfw9puQQo-iehBFrlOp4g.name=Interface P2P
betterquesting.quest.Kcfw9puQQo-iehBFrlOp4g.desc=The §3P2P Interface§r is a P2P device which can be used to easily paralellize recipes across many machines.

# Quest: Energy Cell
betterquesting.quest.Npl3Ifl9RvW8JZRicJaP2A.name=Energy Cell
betterquesting.quest.Npl3Ifl9RvW8JZRicJaP2A.desc=The §3Energy Cell§r acts as a battery for the ME network. It becomes useful when the ME system begins to consume large amounts of energy, so a buffer is needed so it doesnt turn on and off constantly.

# Quest: Modifier Cards
betterquesting.quest.Qxy7Wf9WRnG-vIisndmV0g.name=Modifier Cards
betterquesting.quest.Qxy7Wf9WRnG-vIisndmV0g.desc=§6Modifier Cards§r allow for modification to various ME components, such as speeding them up or being able to toggle them on and off using redstone.

# Quest: Wireless Connectors
betterquesting.quest.ReqBRrKdR2WFSp9ILSPk5w.name=Wireless Connectors
betterquesting.quest.ReqBRrKdR2WFSp9ILSPk5w.desc=§3Wireless Connectors§r allow for channel linking without ME cables, making it possible to send channels through walls. The further away the connectors are the more energy consuming they become.%n%nA §3Wireless Hub§r can be used to link channels between multiple wireless connectors.

# Quest: Network Tool
betterquesting.quest.VE7Ty89_SMW45uAVQdD32g.name=Network Tool
betterquesting.quest.VE7Ty89_SMW45uAVQdD32g.desc=The §6Network Tool§r, when right-clicking on any network device will bring up the tool's interface showing all devices connected to the network as well as network details. As any wrench, shift clicking on a cable will remove it.

# Quest: AE2 Autocrafting
betterquesting.quest.WUUIPZ-KQFCpsXAcpOxwqw.name=AE2 Autocrafting
betterquesting.quest.WUUIPZ-KQFCpsXAcpOxwqw.desc=§2This quest serves an a guide on how to order items using the ME system. The example item will be an Analog Circuit.§r%n%nWith an §3ME Drive§r providing item storage, a §3Crafting CPU§r and §3Interfaces§r, one can request any item to be crafted. The image below makes use of a §3Molecular Assembler§r, a §3Soldering Station§r, an §3Electric Press§r aswell as two §3Import Buses§r which serve as an output for the solderer and press.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_Auto1.png[/img]%n%nThe first step in automating crafting recipes is to encode §6ME Patterns§r. There are two types of patterns, crafting and processing. The crafting pattern is created by having the §3Pattern Terminal§r set to the crafting table. After placing the items in the terminal, press the arrow to finish encoding the recipe.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_Auto2.png[/img]%n%nFor recipes which arent made in a crafting table, such as the §6Wires§r and the §6Analog Circuit§r itself, the pattern terminal needs to be switched to the processing mode, which has a furnace icon.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_Auto3.png[/img]%n%nAfter all the patterns have been created, insert them into their respective interfaces.%nMake sure to enable blocking mode on the interfaces as not to have multiple different recipes enter the interface at once.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_Auto4.png[/img]%n%nFinally, after everything has been set up, the option to order items will be shown in the ME terminal.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_Auto5.png[/img]%n

# Quest: Cell Workbench
betterquesting.quest._RJ-wMmFRWepNEgav4H2ZQ.name=Cell Workbench
betterquesting.quest._RJ-wMmFRWepNEgav4H2ZQ.desc=The §3Cell Workbench§r allow to filter cells to accept specific items. It can prove useful for when making a subnet for §eBedrock Ore Processing§r.

# Quest: ME Storage Bus
betterquesting.quest.b4Wb4VV0RkSBMjTUJj8Idg.name=ME Storage Bus
betterquesting.quest.b4Wb4VV0RkSBMjTUJj8Idg.desc=The §3ME Storage Bus§r, when attached to an block/tile entity with an inventory (generally a storage unit, such as chests or a §3Drawer Controller§r), will include that inventory's contents in the ME System.%n

# Quest: Pattern Capacity Card
betterquesting.quest.d4NudAjPT3G3f26jL0-SaA.name=Pattern Capacity Card
betterquesting.quest.d4NudAjPT3G3f26jL0-SaA.desc=The §6Pattern Capacity Card§r can be used to add 9 more slots for patterns in an §3ME Interface§r. Up to 3 cards can be inserted.

# Quest: Quantum Network Bridge
betterquesting.quest.di_RfA7kSDGB_3iCgsfVaQ.name=Quantum Network Bridge
betterquesting.quest.di_RfA7kSDGB_3iCgsfVaQ.desc=A §3Quantum Network Bridge§r is a multiblock structure that connects 2 potentially distant, or even in different dimensions, network fragments together. Created by crafting 8 §3ME Quantum Ring§r and a §3ME Quantum Link Chamber§r and placing the ME quantum link chamber in the center, and sourrounding it in the 8 ME quantum rings.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Qring1.png[/img]%n%nEach quantum network bridge requires power to function. This power must be provided from the network fragment it is attached to until the bridge is linked; at which time power from either side will be available. However if power is lost, connectivity will fail and power will be drained from the side the bridge is on in attempt to restore connection.%n%nTo establish a link between 2 quantum network bridges, you must create a pair of §6Quantum Entangled Singularities§r. One of each will be placed inside of a particular connection. Each Bridge may only connect to one other bridge.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_Qring2.png[/img]%n%nAE2 Singularities are created by dumping 256k of any block inside a §3Matter Condenser§r. Singularities can become quantum entangled by dropping a singularity and ender dust and then exploding them together.

# Quest: Acceleration Card
betterquesting.quest.g0hMKPOqRWKCKtSyhQtPsA.name=Acceleration Card
betterquesting.quest.g0hMKPOqRWKCKtSyhQtPsA.desc=The §6Acceleration Card§r increases the speed of various AE2 devices.

# Quest: Dense ME Cable
betterquesting.quest.gZL_U2jPTZe5oDt8FcJ2QQ.name=Dense ME Cable
betterquesting.quest.gZL_U2jPTZe5oDt8FcJ2QQ.desc=The §6Dense ME Fluix Cables§r can be used to transmit §e32 channels§r from an §3ME Controller§r.%n%nOne controller is capable of connecting up to 6 dense cables, in turn each can branch off to 4 smaller cable lines connecting up to 192 ME devices to the network.%n%nThe §6Smart Dense Cable§r also displays the amount of channels that are been used, but is known to be less performance friendly than the dense covered cables.%n%nIn addition there are 16 colored cables made with the appropriate dye. The colored cables allow contact with other cables without sharing the signal or connecting to any other cable but the ones of the same colour.

# Quest: Molecular Assembler
betterquesting.quest.h0nPHR-TSQWbZhxIF9pAsA.name=Molecular Assembler
betterquesting.quest.h0nPHR-TSQWbZhxIF9pAsA.desc=The §3Molecular Assembler§r is used to autocraft anything that can be made in a crafting table.

# Quest: Crafting CPU
betterquesting.quest.ku71W0ZTQkOsyV4SQ0pPLA.name=Crafting CPU
betterquesting.quest.ku71W0ZTQkOsyV4SQ0pPLA.desc=The Crafting CPU is a multiblock structure composed of §3Crafting Co-Processing Units§r and §3Crafting Storage§r. When placed next to eachother they form one CPU which is used when placing orders via §3Interfaces§r. The more crafting co-processing units the more tasks the CPU can do in parallel while more crafting storage allows for bigger orders to be made.

# Quest: ME Pattern
betterquesting.quest.lFAX1X73QMiTSYhQ3ozq_g.name=ME Pattern
betterquesting.quest.lFAX1X73QMiTSYhQ3ozq_g.desc=§6ME Patterns§r are used to encode recipes to be used in §3Interfaces§r. They can be encoded in a §3Pattern Terminal§r.

# Quest: ME subnetting
betterquesting.quest.mGns1KltRda4-2iJggTT7w.name=ME subnetting
betterquesting.quest.mGns1KltRda4-2iJggTT7w.desc=§eSubnetworks§r are ME networks which can be accessed from a §eMain Network§r. In §dNTM§r§r they can be useful for storing items from passive processes without flooding the main storage network.%n%n§2This quest serves as a guide on how to set up a subnet, which can be used to store the resourses that Bedrock Ore Processing produces.§r%n%nIn the image below are two ME networks, the §cRed§r one as the §cMainnet§r, and the §9Blue§r one as the §9Subnet§r.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET1.png[/img]%n%nFor the purposes of this quest, the main network will store dirt blocks, while the subnet will store copper blocks.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET2.png[/img]%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET3.png[/img]%n%nTo make the contents of the subnet, the copper blocks, visible to the main net, one must make an §3Interface§r-§3Storage Bus§r§r combo. The storage bus must be on the side of the main network.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET4.png[/img]%n%nMake sure to filter the main network storage bus, and to also make it "Extract Only".%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET5.png[/img]%n%nNow the main network has access to materials stored on the sub network, which can be used for crafting.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/BQ_NET6.png[/img]

# Quest: Network Visualisation Tool
betterquesting.quest.mH0ic-3aRnOZ8FjP-n9qYw.name=Network Visualisation Tool
betterquesting.quest.mH0ic-3aRnOZ8FjP-n9qYw.desc=The §6Network Visualisation Tool§r is used to visuallize an ME Network by right-clicking on any of its blocks, making it very useful when making a large network, especially one that uses §3P2P§r.

# Quest: Overflow Void Card
betterquesting.quest.xyHVMuUHQjSWbujlx1EMqw.name=Overflow Void Card
betterquesting.quest.xyHVMuUHQjSWbujlx1EMqw.desc=The §6Overflow Void Card§r acts as a voiding upgrade for AE2 §6Storage Cells§r. It can be added to a storage cell using the §3Cell Workbench§r.


## Quest Line: OpenComputers
betterquesting.questline.7qWugdC9QfGJ31NktB0YqA.name=OpenComputers
betterquesting.questline.7qWugdC9QfGJ31NktB0YqA.desc=Use OpenComputers to monitor and control complex machinery.

# Quest: Memory
betterquesting.quest.-0Jqqg9TRmCEikNnquKeuA.name=Memory
betterquesting.quest.-0Jqqg9TRmCEikNnquKeuA.desc=§6Memory§r is like the §6CPU§r, an essential part in all computers.%n%nDepending on the CPU's architecture, the memory has a very essential effect on what a computer can and cannot do. For the standard Lua architecture, for example, it controls the actual amount of memory Lua scripts can use. This means that to run larger and more memory-intensive programs, you will need more memory.

# Quest: CPUs
betterquesting.quest.-SW2UUweSLCzJBCGcIm3nw.name=CPUs
betterquesting.quest.-SW2UUweSLCzJBCGcIm3nw.desc=The §6Central Processing Unit§r (CPU), is a core part for each computer or §6Server§r. It defines the architecture of the computer, and the number of components that can be connected to the computer before it stops working. %nHigher tier CPUs also provide a higher per-tick direct call limit to the computer - in simpler terms: better CPUs run faster.

# Quest: Internet Card
betterquesting.quest.1azNAAjWQLaNJLrVXT0W9w.name=Internet Card
betterquesting.quest.1azNAAjWQLaNJLrVXT0W9w.desc=The §6Internet Card§r grants computers access to the internet. It provides ways to perform simple HTTP requests, as well as to open plain TCP client sockets that can be read and written to.%n%nInstalling an internet card in a computer will also attach a custom file system that contains a few internet related applications, such as one for downloading and uploading snippets from/to pastebin as well as a "wget" clone that allows downloading data from arbitrary HTTP URLs.

# Quest: Transistors
betterquesting.quest.43PzmZVaTwS5ZaPt_fhugg.name=Transistors
betterquesting.quest.43PzmZVaTwS5ZaPt_fhugg.desc=The §6Transistor§r is one of the most basic crafting ingredients in OC. It is mainly used to craft §6Microchips§r and other electronic goods.

# Quest: Microchips
betterquesting.quest.5uHqD8E4RmWlcVca_5CJnQ.name=Microchips
betterquesting.quest.5uHqD8E4RmWlcVca_5CJnQ.desc=§6Microchips§r are the bread and butter of electronic component crafting. They come in different tiers, for crafting different tiers of components.

# Quest: Floppy Disks and Disk Drive
betterquesting.quest.6wQAgmUHTxavpGXJvZVhmA.name=Floppy Disks and Disk Drive
betterquesting.quest.6wQAgmUHTxavpGXJvZVhmA.desc=The §3Disk Drive§r can be used to read §6Floppy Disks§r using a computer connected to it.%n%nThis is useful to get started, since the lower tier §3Computer Cases§r do not have a built-in floppy slot, and you'll need an operating system to boot up the computer.

# Quest: Card Base
betterquesting.quest.70KciiqATFCPJR3s6eoIMg.name=Card Base
betterquesting.quest.70KciiqATFCPJR3s6eoIMg.desc=The §6Card Base§r is a common crafting material for card components in OC, such as §6Graphics Cards§r and §6Network Cards§r.

# Quest: Electronic Assembler
betterquesting.quest.7gCyEqlyTQqqnNxQ1cLt-A.name=Electronic Assembler
betterquesting.quest.7gCyEqlyTQqqnNxQ1cLt-A.desc=The §3Electronic Assembler§r is an advanded workstation that can be used to build more complex electronic devices, such as §3Robots§r, §3Drones§r and §6Tablets§r. %n%nThey require a large amount of energy to assemble devices, so it is recommended to power them sufficiently with a §3Capacitor Bank§r.

# Quest: Wireless Network Card
betterquesting.quest.8Bbui0CiRRm3hXTYH-ELpQ.name=Wireless Network Card
betterquesting.quest.8Bbui0CiRRm3hXTYH-ELpQ.desc=The §6Wireless Network Card§r is an upgraded §6Network Card§r that can send and receive wireless network messages.%n %nTier two cards can also send and receive wired messages. The signal strength directly controls the distance up to which a sent message can be received, where the strength is equal to the distance in blocks.

# Quest: Welcome to OC!
betterquesting.quest.90cLqSYpT8OevVo7UEEaGA.name=Welcome to OC!
betterquesting.quest.90cLqSYpT8OevVo7UEEaGA.desc=§dOpenComputers§r is a very useful mod which will let one automate many processes which normaly couldnt be done even with an ME system.%n%nMake sure to always check the §6OC Manual§r as it provides additional information of stuff that the quest book doesnt cover.%n%n§dOpenSecurity§r, §dComputronics§r and §dOpenGlasses§r are also in the pack, expanding whats possible with opencomputers.

# Quest: Control and Arithmetics Units
betterquesting.quest.ABODDDQgRrGXZdmgdHJ7Sg.name=Control and Arithmetics Units
betterquesting.quest.ABODDDQgRrGXZdmgdHJ7Sg.desc=The §6Control Unit§r is used to create §6CPUs§r and §6Component Buses§r.%n%nThe §6Arithmetic Logic Unit§r is used for crafting components that perform calculations, such as CPUs and §6Graphics Cards§r.

# Quest: PWRangler
betterquesting.quest.DkfWKyKpReuU8BkzSMH3Xw.name=PWRangler
betterquesting.quest.DkfWKyKpReuU8BkzSMH3Xw.desc=§dNTM§r offers a built-in §6Floppy Disk§r for monitoring the §3PWR§r reactor.%n%n§2This quest serves as a guide on how to set up an OC Computer using a PWRangler floppy disk.§r%n%nFirst of all, an OC computer with OpenOS must be constructed. For the purposes of this quest the computer that will be used will make use of §bTier 3§r components.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_OC1.png[/img]%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_OC2.png[/img]%n%nAfter booting up the PC, install OpenOS.%n%nOnce the PC has been rebooted, switch out the OpenOS floppy disk with the PWRangler one. Once inserted, type §oinstall§r to install the PWRangler on the system.%n%nThe PWR needs to be linked to the computer using OC Cables directly on the controller.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_OC3.png[/img]%n%nFinally, type §oPWRangler§r in the computer to start the program.%n%n[img height=1000]betterquesting:textures/QB_OC4.png[/img]%n

# Quest: Hard Drives
betterquesting.quest.EdeL97xNTSmiLfPQpCJiow.name=Hard Drives
betterquesting.quest.EdeL97xNTSmiLfPQpCJiow.desc=The §6Hard Disk Drives§r are a higher tier storage medium in OC.%n%nAll storage media perform at the same speed: higher tier storage provides more space. There are also some devices that can only use disk drives (although servers could use an external disk drive, for example). Hard drives can be placed inside a §3Raid§r, allowing multiple drives to share the same file system. Note that placing a hard drive in a raid wipes the drive of its contents.

# Quest: Component Buses
betterquesting.quest.GWpBgrTUR6aiNelNbOLRWQ.name=Component Buses
betterquesting.quest.GWpBgrTUR6aiNelNbOLRWQ.desc=A §6Component Bus§r is a server-specific upgrade that allows the server to communicate with more components at the same time, without shutting down. %n%nLike with §6CPUs§r, higher tier buses provide higher component limits. Higher tier servers are also capable of taking more component buses, allowing for communication with many more components.

# Quest: Servers
betterquesting.quest.QFKT5L7RSrKQIz-qYhUsVg.name=Servers
betterquesting.quest.QFKT5L7RSrKQIz-qYhUsVg.desc=§6Servers§r are a form of higher tier computer. %n%nThey can be configured by holding them in the hand and using them - like opening a backpack for example. Servers can also be configured after having been installed into a Rack by activating them (aiming at the corresponding position on the frong face on the rack). To operate, the server has to be placed inside a §3Rack§r.

# Quest: Computer Casings
betterquesting.quest.XfkIHFJDRgSIyYD_F5b05g.name=Computer Casings
betterquesting.quest.XfkIHFJDRgSIyYD_F5b05g.desc=§3Computer Casings§r come in 3 different tiers, which limit the amount of components that ca be placed inside of them.

# Quest: Graphics Cards
betterquesting.quest.b14L2QcPTRiHysGkQNkTUQ.name=Graphics Cards
betterquesting.quest.b14L2QcPTRiHysGkQNkTUQ.desc=The §6Graphics Card§r is an essential part for most computers and allows the computer to display text on a connected §6Screen§r. %n%nGraphics cards come in several tiers, and like screens, support different resolutions and color depths.

# Quest: Screens
betterquesting.quest.fS6P083FQGWwxARPYM4eaA.name=Screens
betterquesting.quest.fS6P083FQGWwxARPYM4eaA.desc=A §3Screen§r is used in combination with a §6Graphics Card§r, to allow computers to display text. Different screen tiers have different capabilities, such as supporting different resolutions and olor depths. Screens range from low-resolution, monochrome displays to high-resolution displays with up to 256 colors.

# Quest: OC Power
betterquesting.quest.l3OJx_niTg-UyYUoyOXYfg.name=OC Power
betterquesting.quest.l3OJx_niTg-UyYUoyOXYfg.desc=The §6Cable§r serves as a way of connecting computers and machines that are far apart. If you have a compact build where all components touch each other (directly or indirectly, most blocks also behave the same way as cables) you will usually not need cables.%n%nThe §3Power Converter§r serves as the fastest way to convert energy from other mods' power systems to OpenComputers' internal energy. Placing an §3HE to RF Converter§r next to the PC will also work.%n%nThe §3Capacitor Stores§r energy to be used by the network, acting as an energy buffer when needed. It is very useful for tasks that demand a lot of energy, such as assembling or charging devices such as robots and drones.

# Quest: Computer
betterquesting.quest.zElcW5PDQwGOvbKnyroWEQ.name=Computer
betterquesting.quest.zElcW5PDQwGOvbKnyroWEQ.desc=A §3Keyboard§r is needed to type text on §3Screens§r, be they in the world or built into devices such as §3Robots§r or §6Tablets§r.%n%nFor the keyboard to work with a screen in the world, it has to be placed next to the screen, facing that screen, or placed directly on the screen (on top or on one of the sides).%n%nThe §6EEPROM§r is what contains the code used to initialize a computer when it is being booted. %n%nThis data is stored as plain byte array, and may mean different things to different §6CPU§r architectures. For example, for Lua it is usually a small script that searches for a file systems with an init script, for other architectures it may be actual machine code.%n%nAn §6OpenOS Disk§r can be crafted using an empty floppy disk and a manual.


## Quest Line: Building and Decorating
betterquesting.questline.7-1bBIkKRc6xhh5bwIGsjg.name=Building and Decorating
betterquesting.questline.7-1bBIkKRc6xhh5bwIGsjg.desc=Improve your builds by using Chisel, Architecturecraft and Better Builder's Wands.

# Quest: Little Tiles
betterquesting.quest.LUtxXey_T3q_oaUQWXpE7w.name=Little Tiles
betterquesting.quest.LUtxXey_T3q_oaUQWXpE7w.desc=§dLittle Tiles§r is a mod that allows one to make more complex constructs by giving you the ability to make blocks tiny.

# Quest: Chisel
betterquesting.quest.TA6SPr3KTbKsgRFceNMZmA.name=Chisel
betterquesting.quest.TA6SPr3KTbKsgRFceNMZmA.desc=The §6Chisel§r is a building tool which can be used to change the textures of blocks, and even unlock new and unique designs.

# Quest: Schematica
betterquesting.quest.VyF-RUbsSuS8J2hbI5CIkw.name=Schematica
betterquesting.quest.VyF-RUbsSuS8J2hbI5CIkw.desc=With §dSchematica§r, you can create schematics of your builds and post holograms of them on other worlds. Check out the keybinds to get started.

# Quest: Auto Chisel Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.aTDQIHzUSVeuAt9EQuYEZQ.name=Auto Chisel Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.aTDQIHzUSVeuAt9EQuYEZQ.desc=Add some upgrades to the §3Auto Chisel§r to make it go faster.

# Quest: Auto Chisel
betterquesting.quest.alOTKFb0Sbuzhkd7kUHfIQ.name=Auto Chisel
betterquesting.quest.alOTKFb0Sbuzhkd7kUHfIQ.desc=The §3Auto Chisel§r allows for automated chiseling of blocks. Simply insert any chisel in the machine and the block that will act as the template.

# Quest: Ztones
betterquesting.quest.cJN-gv7iQzSfYZQVm1ZyVQ.name=Ztones
betterquesting.quest.cJN-gv7iQzSfYZQVm1ZyVQ.desc=§dZtones§r is another decorative block mod which adds a bunch of unique building blocks.

# Quest: Modern Markings
betterquesting.quest.j9eLuGnhRVWn5uJS_KI5lg.name=Modern Markings
betterquesting.quest.j9eLuGnhRVWn5uJS_KI5lg.desc=§dModern Markings§r adds wall and floor decorations suited for many purposes. Use the §6Chisel§r on the floor or wall signs to change their design.

# Quest: Better Builder's Wands
betterquesting.quest.mPZ8D32cT5WrvlKuPNq90g.name=Better Builder's Wands
betterquesting.quest.mPZ8D32cT5WrvlKuPNq90g.desc=The §6Building Wand§r allows one to place many blocks at once, making walls and roads easier to construct. The stronger material the wand is made out of, the more blocks it can place.%n%n§2To replace water blocks using wands bind the key, Change Fluid Mode, in settings.

# Quest: ArchitectureCraft
betterquesting.quest.p7NNm2NvRgWz37LQO6yraw.name=ArchitectureCraft
betterquesting.quest.p7NNm2NvRgWz37LQO6yraw.desc=§dArchitectureCraft§r introduces the §3Architect's Workbench§r which can be used to change the shapes blocks.%n%nThe §6Architect's Hammer§r can be used to easily rotate the blocks.%n%nThe §6Architect's Glowbrush§r can be used to apply light to any block.%n%nThe §6Architect's Chisel§r is used to pick up blocks such as glass and glowstone without breaking them by right-clicking.

# Quest: Sign Pictures
betterquesting.quest.wAu-q390TlKihyp-bEI2lw.name=Sign Pictures
betterquesting.quest.wAu-q390TlKihyp-bEI2lw.desc=The §dSignPicture§r mod allows one to put any image on a sign, opening the door to many unique building designs. Press \ to get started.


### Quests in multiple quest lines ###

# Quest: Antimatter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGw.name=Antimatter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGw.desc=§bAntimatter§r is a dangerous substance which can be obtained from a §3Cyclotron§r or a §3Particle Accelerator§r. If dropped on the floor a violent explosion will occur. Antimatter cant be stored in normal tanks, and as such, a §3Magnetic Antimatter Container§r is required.

# Quest: Bedrock Ore Extracting
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALA.name=Bedrock Ore Extracting
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALA.desc=§eBedrock Ore Deposits§r are an infinite source of resourses which can be obtained by using a §3Large Mining Drill§r and a §3Bedrock Ore Processor§r.%n%nOperating the drill will consume§e 200kHE/s§r.%n%nBefore excavation can happen, the §eDepth Rock§r covering the bedrock ore deposit needs to be removed. An easy way of doing that is blowing up the rock with §6Mining Charges§r.%n%nThe large mining drill is used to excavate §6Raw Bedrock Ores§r from their deposits. The drill requires a §6Drillbit§r to work§r, which can be upgraded to increase the speed at which it operates at. §eFortune§r on a drillbit affects the quality of mined bedrock ore, each level of fortune adds §e10%%§r of the value to the item.%n%nThe bedrock ore processor takes §6§rraw bedrock ore obtained from the drill and breaks it down into smaller pieces, each with different products that can be obtained from them. %n§a§bOre Slop§r, which is created when the machine is operating, can be processed into many useful products, especially when it is sent through an §3Electrolysis Machine§r.%n%nThe §6Bedrock Ore Density Scanner§r shows information on the composition of Bedrock Ore deposits.%n%nBedrock ore processing can be both an energy and resourse expensive operation so it is recommended that it is explored after having good infrastructure.%n%n§2Consider adding a Power Saving Upgrade to the drill as it only reduces power without affecting the mining speed. Additionally, installing an Effectiveness Upgrade on the ore slopper will make it give out more resourses.§r§r%n%nIt is recommended that the wiki is checked out.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Bedrock_Ore[/url]

# Quest: Particle Accelerator
betterquesting.quest._nmJ1zrSQp22psctX6Uq2A.name=Particle Accelerator
betterquesting.quest._nmJ1zrSQp22psctX6Uq2A.desc=The §3Particle Accelerator§r is a highly modular machine that uses high strength superconducting magnets to accelerate particles to relativistic speeds in order to collide them together.%n%nDue to the complex and expansive nature of the particle accelerator, it is highly recommend that the wiki is checked out as it provides more information.%n%n[url]https://nucleartech.wiki/wiki/Particle_Accelerator[/url]%n%n§2This quest demands the most essential parts of the particle accelerator, and does not represent the amount needed for it to function.


